{'text': "Directive\n2001/14/EC\nof\nthe\nEuropean\nParliament\nand\nof\nthe\nCouncil\nof\n26\nFebruary\n2001\non\nthe\nallocation\nof\nrailway\ninfrastructure\ncapacity\nand\nthe\nlevying\nof\ncharges\nfor\nthe\nuse\nof\nrailway\ninfrastructure\nand\nsafety\ncertification\nTHE\nEUROPEAN\nPARLIAMENT\nAND\nTHE\nCOUNCIL\nOF\nTHE\nEUROPEAN\nUNION\n,\nHaving\nregard\nto\nthe\nTreaty\nestablishing\nthe\nEuropean\nCommunity\n,\nand\nin\nparticular\nArticle\n71\nthereof\n,\nHaving\nregard\nto\nthe\nproposal\nfrom\nthe\nCommission\n(\n1\n)\n,\nHaving\nregard\nto\nthe\nopinion\nof\nthe\nEconomic\nand\nSocial\nCommittee\n(\n2\n)\n,\nHaving\nregard\nto\nthe\nopinion\nof\nthe\nCommittee\nof\nthe\nRegions\n(\n3\n)\n,\nActing\nin\naccordance\nwith\nthe\nprocedure\nlaid\ndown\nin\nArticle\n251\nof\nthe\nTreaty\n(\n4\n)\nin\nthe\nlight\nof\nthe\njoint\ntext\napproved\non\n22\nNovember\n2000\nby\nthe\nConciliation\nCommittee\n,\nWhereas\n:\n(\n1\n)\nGreater\nintegration\nof\nthe\nCommunity\nrailway\nsector\nis\nan\nessential\nelement\nof\nthe\ncompletion\nof\nthe\ninternal\nmarket\nand\nmoving\ntowards\nachieving\nsustainable\nmobility\n.\n(\n2\n)\nCouncil\nDirective\n91/440/EEC\nof\n29\nJuly\n1991\non\nthe\ndevelopment\nof\nthe\nCommunity\n's\nrailways\n(\n5\n)\nprovides\nfor\ncertain\naccess\nrights\nin\ninternational\nrail\ntransport\nfor\nrailway\nundertakings\n,\nand\ninternational\ngroupings\nof\nrailway\nundertakings\n;\nthese\nrights\nmean\nthat\nrailway\ninfrastructure\ncan\nbe\nused\nby\nmultiple\nusers\n.\n(\n3\n)\nCouncil\nDirective\n95/19/EC\nof\n19\nJune\n1995\non\nthe\nallocation\nof\nrailway\ninfrastructure\ncapacity\nand\nthe\ncharging\nof\ninfrastructure\nfees\n(\n6\n)\nset\nout\na\nbroad\nframework\nfor\nthe\nallocation\nof\nrailway\ninfrastructure\ncapacity\n.\n(\n4\n)\nThose\nDirectives\nhave\nnot\nprevented\na\nconsiderable\nvariation\nin\nthe\nstructure\nand\nlevel\nof\nrailway\ninfrastructure\ncharges\nand\nthe\nform\nand\nduration\nof\ncapacity\nallocation\nprocesses\n.\n(\n5\n)\nTo\nensure\ntransparency\nand\nnon-discriminatory\naccess\nto\nrail\ninfrastructure\nfor\nall\nrailway\nundertakings\nall\nthe\nnecessary\ninformation\nrequired\nto\nuse\naccess\nrights\nare\nto\nbe\npublished\nin\na\nnetwork\nstatement\n.\n(\n6\n)\nAppropriate\ncapacity-allocation\nschemes\nfor\nrail\ninfrastructure\ncoupled\nwith\ncompetitive\noperators\nwill\nresult\nin\na\nbetter\nbalance\nof\ntransport\nbetween\nmodes\n.\n(\n7\n)\nEncouraging\noptimal\nuse\nof\nthe\nrailway\ninfrastructure\nwill\nlead\nto\na\nreduction\nin\nthe\ncost\nof\ntransport\nto\nsociety\n.\n(\n8\n)\nAn\nefficient\nfreight\nsector\n,\nespecially\nacross\nborders\n,\nrequires\naction\nfor\nthe\nopening\nup\nof\nthe\nmarket\n.\n(\n9\n)\nIt\nshould\nbe\npossible\nfor\nMember\nStates\nto\nallow\npurchasers\nof\nrailway\nservices\nto\nenter\ndirectly\nthe\ncapacity-allocation\nprocess\n.\n(\n10\n)\nThe\nrevitalisation\nof\nEuropean\nrailways\nby\nmeans\nof\nextended\naccess\nfor\ninternational\nfreight\non\nthe\nTrans-European\nRail\nFreight\nNetwork\nrequires\nfair\nintermodal\ncompetition\nbetween\nrail\nand\nroad\n,\nparticularly\nby\ntaking\nappropriate\naccount\nof\nthe\ndifferent\nexternal\neffects\n;\nappropriate\ncharging\nschemes\nfor\nrail\ninfrastructure\ncoupled\nwith\nappropriate\ncharging\nschemes\nfor\nother\ntransport\ninfrastructures\nand\ncompetitive\noperators\nwill\nresult\nin\nan\noptimal\nbalance\nof\ndifferent\ntransport\nmodes\n.\n(\n11\n)\nThe\ncharging\nand\ncapacity\nallocation\nschemes\nshould\npermit\nequal\nand\nnon-discriminatory\naccess\nfor\nall\nundertakings\nand\nattempt\nas\nfar\nas\npossible\nto\nmeet\nthe\nneeds\nof\nall\nusers\nand\ntraffic\ntypes\nin\na\nfair\nand\nnon-discriminatory\nmanner\n.\n(\n12\n)\nWithin\nthe\nframework\nset\nout\nby\nMember\nStates\ncharging\nand\ncapacity-allocation\nschemes\nshould\nencourage\nrailway\ninfrastructure\nmanagers\nto\noptimise\nuse\nof\ntheir\ninfrastructure\n.\n(\n13\n)\nRailway\nundertakings\nshould\nreceive\nclear\nand\nconsistent\nsignals\nfrom\ncapacity\nallocation\nschemes\nwhich\nlead\nthem\nto\nmake\nrational\ndecisions\n.\n(\n14\n)\nIn\norder\nto\ntake\ninto\naccount\nthe\nneeds\nof\nusers\n,\nor\npotential\nusers\n,\nof\nrailway\ninfrastructure\ncapacity\nto\nplan\ntheir\nbusiness\n,\nand\nto\nthe\nneeds\nof\ncustomers\nand\nfunders\n,\nit\nis\nimportant\nthat\nthe\ninfrastructure\nmanager\nensures\nthat\ninfrastructure\ncapacity\nis\nallocated\nin\na\nway\nwhich\nreflects\nthe\nneed\nto\nmaintain\nand\nimprove\nservice\nreliability\nlevels\n.\n(\n15\n)\nIt\nis\ndesirable\nfor\nrailway\nundertakings\nand\nthe\ninfrastructure\nmanager\nto\nbe\nprovided\nwith\nincentives\nto\nminimise\ndisruption\nand\nimprove\nperformance\nof\nthe\nnetwork\n.\n(\n16\n)\nCharging\nand\ncapacity\nallocation\nschemes\nshould\nallow\nfor\nfair\ncompetition\nin\nthe\nprovision\nof\nrailway\nservices\n.\n(\n17\n)\nIt\nis\nimportant\nto\nhave\nregard\nto\nthe\nbusiness\nrequirements\nof\nboth\napplicants\nand\nthe\ninfrastructure\nmanager\n.\n(\n18\n)\nIt\nis\nimportant\nto\nmaximise\nthe\nflexibility\navailable\nto\nthe\ninfrastructure\nmanagers\nwith\nregard\nto\nthe\nallocation\nof\ninfrastructure\ncapacity\n,\nbut\nthis\nmust\nbe\nconsistent\nwith\nsatisfaction\nof\nthe\napplicant\n's\nreasonable\nrequirements\n.\n(\n19\n)\nThe\ncapacity\nallocation\nprocess\nmust\nprevent\nthe\nimposition\nof\nundue\nconstraints\non\nthe\nwishes\nof\nother\nundertakings\nholding\n,\nor\nintending\nto\nhold\n,\nrights\nto\nuse\nthe\ninfrastructure\nto\ndevelop\ntheir\nbusiness\n.\n(\n20\n)\nIt\nis\ndesirable\nto\ngrant\nsome\ndegree\nof\nflexibility\nto\ninfrastructure\nmanagers\nto\nenable\na\nmore\nefficient\nuse\nto\nbe\nmade\nof\nthe\ninfrastructure\nnetwork\n.\n(\n21\n)\nCapacity\nallocation\nand\ncharging\nschemes\nmay\nneed\nto\ntake\naccount\nof\nthe\nfact\nthat\ndifferent\ncomponents\nof\nthe\nrail\ninfrastructure\nnetwork\nmay\nhave\nbeen\ndesigned\nwith\ndifferent\nprincipal\nusers\nin\nmind\n.\n(\n22\n)\nThe\nrequirements\nfor\npassenger\nservices\nmay\noften\nconflict\nwith\nthe\nrequirements\nfor\nfreight\n;\nthe\nrequirements\nfor\npassenger\nservices\nmay\nresult\nin\na\nnetwork\nwhich\nis\nmore\ncostly\nto\nbuild\nand\nmaintain\nthan\none\ndesigned\nsolely\nfor\nfreight\n;\nthe\nincreasing\nspeed\ndifferential\nbetween\nfreight\nand\npassenger\nrolling\nstock\ncan\nlead\nto\nan\nexacerbation\nof\nthe\nconflict\nbetween\nthese\ntwo\ntypes\nof\ntraffic\n.\n(\n23\n)\nDifferent\nusers\nand\ntypes\nof\nusers\nwill\nfrequently\nhave\na\ndifferent\nimpact\non\ninfrastructure\ncapacity\nand\nthe\nneeds\nof\ndifferent\nservices\nneed\nto\nbe\nproperly\nbalanced\n.\n(\n24\n)\nServices\noperated\nunder\ncontract\nto\na\npublic\nauthority\nmay\nrequire\nspecial\nrules\nto\nsafeguard\ntheir\nattractiveness\nto\nusers\n.\n(\n25\n)\nThe\ncharging\nand\ncapacity\nallocation\nschemes\nmust\ntake\naccount\nof\nthe\neffects\nof\nincreasing\nsaturation\nof\ninfrastructure\ncapacity\nand\nultimately\nthe\nscarcity\nof\ncapacity\n.\n(\n26\n)\nThe\ndifferent\ntime-frames\nfor\nplanning\ntraffic\ntypes\nmean\nthat\nit\nis\ndesirable\nto\nensure\nthat\nrequests\nfor\ninfrastructure\ncapacity\nwhich\nare\nmade\nafter\nthe\ncompletion\nof\nthe\ntimetabling\nprocess\ncan\nbe\nsatisfied\n.\n(\n27\n)\nThe\nuse\nof\ninformation\ntechnology\ncan\nenhance\nthe\nspeed\nand\nresponsiveness\nof\nthe\ntimetabling\nprocess\nand\nimprove\nthe\nability\nof\napplicants\nto\nbid\nfor\ninfrastructure\ncapacity\n,\nas\nwell\nas\nimproving\nthe\nability\nto\nestablish\ntrain\npaths\nwhich\ncross\nmore\nthan\none\ninfrastructure\nmanager\n's\nnetwork\n.\n(\n28\n)\nTo\nensure\nthe\noptimum\noutcome\nfor\nrailway\nundertakings\n,\nit\nis\ndesirable\nto\nrequire\nan\nexamination\nof\nthe\nuse\nof\ninfrastructure\ncapacity\nwhen\nthe\ncoordination\nof\nrequests\nfor\ncapacity\nis\nrequired\nto\nmeet\nthe\nneeds\nof\nusers\n.\n(\n29\n)\nIn\nview\nof\nthe\nmonopolistic\nposition\nof\nthe\ninfrastructure\nmanagers\nit\nis\ndesirable\nto\nrequire\nan\nexamination\nof\nthe\navailable\ninfrastructure\ncapacity\n,\nand\nmethods\nof\nenhancing\nit\nwhen\nthe\ncapacity\nallocation\nprocess\nis\nunable\nto\nmeet\nthe\nrequirements\nof\nusers\n.\n(\n30\n)\nA\nlack\nof\ninformation\nabout\nother\nrailway\nundertakings\n'\nrequests\nas\nwell\nas\nabout\nthe\nconstraints\nwithin\nthe\nsystem\nmay\nmake\nit\ndifficult\nfor\nrailway\nundertakings\nto\nseek\nto\noptimise\ntheir\ninfrastructure\ncapacity\nrequests\n.\n(\n31\n)\nIt\nis\nimportant\nto\nensure\nthe\nbetter\ncoordination\nof\nallocation\nschemes\nso\nas\nto\nensure\nthe\nimproved\nattractiveness\nof\nrail\nfor\ntraffic\nwhich\nuses\nthe\nnetwork\nof\nmore\nthan\none\ninfrastructure\nmanager\n,\nin\nparticular\nfor\ninternational\ntraffic\n.\n(\n32\n)\nIt\nis\nimportant\nto\nminimise\nthe\ndistortions\nof\ncompetition\nwhich\nmay\narise\n,\neither\nbetween\nrailway\ninfrastructures\nor\nbetween\ntransport\nmodes\n,\nfrom\nsignificant\ndifferences\nin\ncharging\nprinciples\n.\n(\n33\n)\nIt\nis\ndesirable\nto\ndefine\nthose\ncomponents\nof\nthe\ninfrastructure\nservice\nwhich\nare\nessential\nto\nenable\nan\noperator\nto\nprovide\na\nservice\nand\nwhich\nshould\nbe\nprovided\nin\nreturn\nfor\nminimum\naccess\ncharges\n.\n(\n34\n)\nInvestment\nin\nrailway\ninfrastructure\nis\ndesirable\nand\ninfrastructure\ncharging\nschemes\nshould\nprovide\nincentives\nfor\ninfrastructure\nmanagers\nto\nmake\nappropriate\ninvestments\nwhere\nthey\nare\neconomically\nattractive\n.\n(\n35\n)\nAny\ncharging\nscheme\nwill\nsend\neconomic\nsignals\nto\nusers\n.\nIt\nis\nimportant\nthat\nthose\nsignals\nto\nrailway\nundertakings\nshould\nbe\nconsistent\nand\nlead\nthem\nto\nmake\nrational\ndecisions\n.\n(\n36\n)\nTo\nenable\nthe\nestablishment\nof\nappropriate\nand\nfair\nlevels\nof\ninfrastructure\ncharges\n,\ninfrastructure\nmanagers\nneed\nto\nrecord\nand\nestablish\nthe\nvaluation\nof\ntheir\nassets\nand\ndevelop\na\nclear\nunderstanding\nof\ncost\nfactors\nin\nthe\noperation\nof\nthe\ninfrastructure\n.\n(\n37\n)\nIt\nis\ndesirable\nto\nensure\nthat\naccount\nis\ntaken\nof\nexternal\ncosts\nwhen\nmaking\ntransport\ndecisions\n.\n(\n38\n)\nIt\nis\nimportant\nto\nensure\nthat\ncharges\nfor\ninternational\ntraffic\nare\nsuch\nas\nto\npermit\nrail\nto\nmeet\nthe\nneeds\nof\nthe\nmarket\n;\nconsequently\ninfrastructure\ncharging\nshould\nbe\nset\nat\nthe\ncost\nthat\nis\ndirectly\nincurred\nas\na\nresult\nof\noperating\nthe\ntrain\nservice\n.\n(\n39\n)\nThe\noverall\nlevel\nof\ncost\nrecovery\nthrough\ninfrastructure\ncharges\naffects\nthe\nnecessary\nlevel\nof\ngovernment\ncontribution\n;\nMember\nStates\nmay\nrequire\ndifferent\nlevels\nof\noverall\ncost\nrecovery\nthrough\ncharges\nincluding\nmark-ups\nor\na\nrate\nof\nreturn\nwhich\nthe\nmarket\ncan\nbear\nwhile\nbalancing\ncost\nrecovery\nwith\nintermodal\ncompetitiveness\nof\nrail\nfreight\n.\nHowever\n,\nit\nis\ndesirable\nfor\nany\ninfrastructure\ncharging\nscheme\nto\nenable\ntraffic\nto\nuse\nthe\nrail\nnetwork\nwhich\ncan\nat\nleast\npay\nfor\nthe\nadditional\ncost\nwhich\nit\nimposes\n.\n(\n40\n)\nA\nrailway\ninfrastructure\nis\na\nnatural\nmonopoly\n.\nIt\nis\ntherefore\nnecessary\nto\nprovide\ninfrastructure\nmanagers\nwith\nincentives\nto\nreduce\ncosts\nand\nmanage\ntheir\ninfrastructure\nefficiently\n.\n(\n41\n)\nAccount\nshould\nbe\ntaken\nof\nthe\nfact\nthat\nfor\na\ngreat\nmany\nyears\nthe\nlevel\nof\ninvestment\nin\ninfrastructure\nand\ntechnology\nhas\nnot\nmade\nit\npossible\nto\ncreate\nthe\nconditions\nfor\nany\nreal\ndevelopment\nof\nrailway\ntransport\n.\nIt\nis\ntherefore\nadvisable\n,\nagainst\nthis\nbackground\n,\nfor\nappropriate\nupgrading\nto\nbe\ncarried\nout\n,\nin\nparticular\nin\nthe\ncontext\nof\nsetting\nup\nthe\nTrans-European\nRail\nFreight\nNetwork\n,\nby\nusing\ninter\nalia\nthe\nCommunity\ninstruments\navailable\n,\nwithout\nprejudice\nto\npriorities\nalready\nestablished\n.\n(\n42\n)\nDiscounts\nwhich\nare\nallowed\nto\nrailway\nundertakings\nmust\nrelate\nto\nactual\nadministrative\ncost\nsavings\nexperienced\n;\ndiscounts\nmay\nalso\nbe\nused\nto\npromote\nthe\nefficient\nuse\nof\ninfrastructure\n.\n(\n43\n)\nIt\nis\ndesirable\nfor\nrailway\nundertakings\nand\nthe\ninfrastructure\nmanager\nto\nbe\nprovided\nwith\nincentives\nto\nminimise\ndisruption\nof\nthe\nnetwork\n.\n(\n44\n)\nThe\nallocation\nof\ncapacity\nis\nassociated\nwith\na\ncost\nto\nthe\ninfrastructure\nmanager\n,\npayment\nfor\nwhich\nshould\nbe\nrequired\n.\n(\n45\n)\nMeasures\nare\nneeded\nto\nensure\nthat\nall\nrailway\nundertakings\nlicensed\nunder\nCommunity\nlaw\nare\nrequired\nto\nhold\nan\nappropriate\nsafety\ncertificate\nbefore\noperating\non\nthe\nterritory\nof\na\nMember\nState\n;\nthe\ngranting\nof\nsafety\ncertificates\nmust\ncomply\nwith\nCommunity\nlaw\n.\n(\n46\n)\nThe\nefficient\nmanagement\nand\nfair\nand\nnon-discriminatory\nuse\nof\nrail\ninfrastructure\nrequire\nthe\nestablishment\nof\na\nregulatory\nbody\nthat\noversees\nthe\napplication\nof\nthese\nCommunity\nrules\nand\nacts\nas\nan\nappeal\nbody\n,\nnotwithstanding\nthe\npossibility\nof\njudicial\nreview\n.\n(\n47\n)\nSpecific\nmeasures\nare\nrequired\nto\ntake\naccount\nof\nthe\nspecific\ngeopolitical\nand\ngeographical\nsituation\nof\ncertain\nMember\nStates\nas\nwell\nas\na\nspecific\norganisation\nof\nthe\nrailway\nsector\nin\nvarious\nMember\nStates\nwhile\nensuring\nthe\nintegrity\nof\nthe\ninternal\nmarket\n.\n(\n48\n)\nThe\nmeasures\nnecessary\nfor\nthe\nimplementation\nof\nthis\nDirective\nshould\nbe\nadopted\nin\naccordance\nwith\nCouncil\nDecision\n1999/468/EC\nof\n28\nJune\n1999\nlaying\ndown\nthe\nprocedures\nfor\nthe\nexercise\nof\nimplementing\npowers\nconferred\non\nthe\nCommission\n(\n7\n)\n.\n(\n49\n)\nIn\naccordance\nwith\nthe\nprinciples\nof\nsubsidiarity\nand\nproportionality\nas\nset\nout\nin\nArticle\n5\nof\nthe\nTreaty\n,\nthe\nobjectives\nof\nthis\nDirective\n,\nnamely\nto\ncoordinate\narrangements\nin\nthe\nMember\nStates\ngoverning\nthe\nallocation\nof\nrailway\ninfrastructure\ncapacity\nand\nthe\ncharges\nmade\nfor\nthe\nuse\nthereof\nas\nwell\nas\nsafety\ncertification\n,\ncan\nnot\nbe\nsufficiently\nachieved\nby\nthe\nMember\nStates\nin\nview\nof\nthe\nneed\nto\nensure\nfair\nand\nnon-discriminatory\nterms\nfor\naccess\nto\nthe\ninfrastructure\nas\nwell\nas\nto\ntake\naccount\nof\nthe\nmanifestly\ninternational\ndimensions\ninvolved\nin\nthe\noperation\nof\nsignificant\nelements\nof\nthe\nrailway\nnetworks\n,\nand\ncan\ntherefore\n,\nby\nreason\nof\nthe\nneed\nfor\ncoordinated\ntrans-national\naction\n,\nbe\nbetter\nachieved\nby\nthe\nCommunity\n.\nThis\nDirective\ndoes\nnot\ngo\nbeyond\nwhat\nis\nnecessary\nto\nachieve\nthose\nobjectives\n.\n(\n50\n)\nCouncil\nRegulation\n(\nEEC\n)\nNo\n2830/77\nof\n12\nDecember\n1977\non\nthe\nmeasures\nnecessary\nto\nachieve\ncomparability\nbetween\nthe\naccounting\nsystems\nand\nannual\naccounts\nof\nrailway\nundertakings\n(\n8\n)\n,\nCouncil\nRegulation\n(\nEEC\n)\nNo\n2183/78\nof\n19\nSeptember\n1978\nlaying\ndown\nuniform\ncosting\nprinciples\nfor\nrailway\nundertakings\n(\n9\n)\n,\nCouncil\nDecision\n82/529/EEC\nof\n19\nJuly\n1982\non\nthe\nfixing\nof\nrates\nfor\nthe\ninternational\ncarriage\nof\ngoods\nby\nrail\n(\n10\n)\n,\nCouncil\nDecision\n83/418/EEC\nof\n25\nJuly\n1983\non\nthe\ncommercial\nindependence\nof\nthe\nrailways\nin\nthe\nmanagement\nof\ntheir\ninternational\npassenger\nand\nluggage\ntraffic\n(\n11\n)\n,\nand\nDirective\n95/19/EC\nare\nsuperseded\nby\nthis\nDirective\nand\nshould\ntherefore\nbe\nrepealed\n,\nHAVE\nADOPTED\nTHIS\nDIRECTIVE\n:\nCHAPTER\nI\nINTRODUCTORY\nPROVISIONS\nArticle\n1\nScope\n1\n.\nThis\nDirective\nconcerns\nthe\nprinciples\nand\nprocedures\nto\nbe\napplied\nwith\nregard\nto\nthe\nsetting\nand\ncharging\nof\nrailway\ninfrastructure\ncharges\nand\nthe\nallocation\nof\nrailway\ninfrastructure\ncapacity\n.\nMember\nStates\nshall\nensure\nthat\ncharging\nand\ncapacity\nallocation\nschemes\nfor\nrailway\ninfrastructure\nfollow\nthe\nprinciples\nset\ndown\nin\nthis\nDirective\nand\nthus\nallow\nthe\ninfrastructure\nmanager\nto\nmarket\nand\nmake\noptimum\neffective\nuse\nof\nthe\navailable\ninfrastructure\ncapacity\n.\n2\n.\nThis\nDirective\napplies\nto\nthe\nuse\nof\nrailway\ninfrastructure\nfor\ndomestic\nand\ninternational\nrail\nservices\n.\n3\n.\nMember\nStates\nmay\nexclude\nfrom\nthe\nscope\nof\nthis\nDirective\n:\na\n)\nstand-alone\nlocal\nand\nregional\nnetworks\nfor\npassenger\nservices\non\nrailway\ninfrastructure\n;\nb\n)\nnetworks\nintended\nonly\nfor\nthe\noperation\nof\nurban\nor\nsuburban\npassenger\nservices\n;\nc\n)\nregional\nnetworks\nwhich\nare\nused\nfor\nregional\nfreight\nservices\nsolely\nby\na\nrailway\nundertaking\nthat\nis\nnot\ncovered\nby\nthe\nscope\nof\nDirective\n91/440/EEC\nuntil\ncapacity\non\nthat\nnetwork\nis\nrequested\nby\nanother\napplicant\n;\nd\n)\nprivately\nowned\nrailway\ninfrastructure\nthat\nexists\nsolely\nfor\nuse\nby\nthe\ninfrastructure\nowner\nfor\nits\nown\nfreight\noperations\n.\n4\n.\nTransport\noperations\nin\nthe\nform\nof\nshuttle\nservices\nfor\nroad\nvehicles\nthrough\nthe\nChannel\nTunnel\nare\nexcluded\nfrom\nthe\nscope\nof\nthis\nDirective\n.\nArticle\n2\nDefinitions\nFor\nthe\npurpose\nof\nthis\nDirective\n:\na\n)\n``\nallocation\n''\nmeans\nthe\nallocation\nof\nrailway\ninfrastructure\ncapacity\nby\nan\ninfrastructure\nmanager\n;\nb\n)\n``\napplicant\n''\nmeans\na\nlicensed\nrailway\nundertaking\nand/or\nan\ninternational\ngrouping\nof\nrailway\nundertakings\n,\nand\n,\nin\nMember\nStates\nwhich\nprovide\nfor\nsuch\na\npossibility\n,\nother\npersons\nand/or\nlegal\nentities\nwith\npublic\nservice\nor\ncommercial\ninterest\nin\nprocuring\ninfrastructure\ncapacity\n,\nsuch\nas\npublic\nauthorities\nunder\nRegulation\n(\nEEC\n)\nNo\n1191/69\n(\n12\n)\nand\nshippers\n,\nfreight\nforwarders\nand\ncombined\ntransport\noperators\n,\nfor\nthe\noperation\nof\nrailway\nservice\non\ntheir\nrespective\nterritories\n;\nc\n)\n``\ncongested\ninfrastructure\n''\nmeans\na\nsection\nof\ninfrastructure\nfor\nwhich\ndemand\nfor\ninfrastructure\ncapacity\ncan\nnot\nbe\nfully\nsatisfied\nduring\ncertain\nperiods\neven\nafter\ncoordination\nof\nthe\ndifferent\nrequests\nfor\ncapacity\n;\nd\n)\n``\ncapacity\nenhancement\nplan\n''\nmeans\na\nmeasure\nor\nseries\nof\nmeasures\nwith\na\ncalendar\nfor\ntheir\nimplementation\nwhich\nare\nproposed\nto\nalleviate\nthe\ncapacity\nconstraints\nleading\nto\nthe\ndeclaration\nof\na\nsection\nof\ninfrastructure\nas\n``\ncongested\ninfrastructure\n''\n;\ne\n)\n``\ncoordination\n''\nmeans\nthe\nprocess\nthrough\nwhich\nthe\nallocation\nbody\nand\napplicants\nwill\nattempt\nto\nresolve\nsituations\nin\nwhich\nthere\nare\nconflicting\napplications\nfor\ninfrastructure\ncapacity\n;\nf\n)\n``\nframework\nagreement\n''\nmeans\na\nlegally\nbinding\ngeneral\nagreement\non\nthe\nbasis\nof\npublic\nor\nprivate\nlaw\n,\nsetting\nout\nthe\nrights\nand\nobligations\nof\nan\napplicant\nand\nthe\ninfrastructure\nmanager\nor\nthe\nallocation\nbody\nin\nrelation\nto\nthe\ninfrastructure\ncapacity\nto\nbe\nallocated\nand\nthe\ncharges\nto\nbe\nlevied\nover\na\nperiod\nlonger\nthan\none\nworking\ntimetable\nperiod\n;\ng\n)\n``\ninfrastructure\ncapacity\n''\nmeans\nthe\npotential\nto\nschedule\ntrain\npaths\nrequested\nfor\nan\nelement\nof\ninfrastructure\nfor\na\ncertain\nperiod\n;\nh\n)\n``\ninfrastructure\nmanager\n''\nmeans\nany\nbody\nor\nundertaking\nthat\nis\nresponsible\nin\nparticular\nfor\nestablishing\nand\nmaintaining\nrailway\ninfrastructure\n.\nThis\nmay\nalso\ninclude\nthe\nmanagement\nof\ninfrastructure\ncontrol\nand\nsafety\nsystems\n.\nThe\nfunctions\nof\nthe\ninfrastructure\nmanager\non\na\nnetwork\nor\npart\nof\na\nnetwork\nmay\nbe\nallocated\nto\ndifferent\nbodies\nor\nundertakings\n;\ni\n)\n``\nnetwork\n''\nmeans\nthe\nentire\nrailway\ninfrastructure\nowned\nand/or\nmanaged\nby\nan\ninfrastructure\nmanager\n;\nj\n)\n``\nnetwork\nstatement\n''\nmeans\nthe\nstatement\nwhich\nsets\nout\nin\ndetail\nthe\ngeneral\nrules\n,\ndeadlines\n,\nprocedures\nand\ncriteria\nconcerning\nthe\ncharging\nand\ncapacity\nallocation\nschemes\n.\nIt\nshall\nalso\ncontain\nsuch\nother\ninformation\nas\nis\nrequired\nto\nenable\napplication\nfor\ninfrastructure\ncapacity\n;\nk\n)\n``\nrailway\nundertaking\n''\nmeans\nany\npublic\nor\nprivate\nundertaking\n,\nlicensed\naccording\nto\napplicable\nCommunity\nlegislation\n,\nthe\nprincipal\nbusiness\nof\nwhich\nis\nto\nprovide\nservices\nfor\nthe\ntransport\nof\ngoods\nand/or\npassengers\nby\nrail\nwith\na\nrequirement\nthat\nthe\nundertaking\nmust\nensure\ntraction\n;\nthis\nalso\nincludes\nundertakings\nwhich\nprovide\ntraction\nonly\n;\nl\n)\n``\ntrain\npath\n''\nmeans\nthe\ninfrastructure\ncapacity\nneeded\nto\nrun\na\ntrain\nbetween\ntwo\nplaces\nover\na\ngiven\ntime-period\n;\nm\n)\n``\nworking\ntimetable\n''\nmeans\nthe\ndata\ndefining\nall\nplanned\ntrain\nand\nrolling-stock\nmovements\nwhich\nwill\ntake\nplace\non\nthe\nrelevant\ninfrastructure\nduring\nthe\nperiod\nfor\nwhich\nit\nis\nin\nforce\n.\nArticle\n3\nNetwork\nstatement\n1\n.\nThe\ninfrastructure\nmanager\nshall\n,\nafter\nconsultation\nwith\nthe\ninterested\nparties\n,\ndevelop\nand\npublish\na\nnetwork\nstatement\nobtainable\nagainst\npayment\nof\na\nduty\nwhich\nmay\nnot\nexceed\nthe\ncost\nof\npublishing\nthat\nstatement\n.\n2\n.\nThe\nnetwork\nstatement\nshall\nset\nout\nthe\nnature\nof\nthe\ninfrastructure\nwhich\nis\navailable\nto\nrailway\nundertakings\n.\nIt\nshall\ncontain\ninformation\nsetting\nout\nthe\nconditions\nfor\naccess\nto\nthe\nrelevant\nrailway\ninfrastructure\n.\nThe\ncontent\nof\nthe\nnetwork\nstatement\nis\nlaid\ndown\nin\nAnnex\nI\n.\n3\n.\nThe\nnetwork\nstatement\nshall\nbe\nkept\nup\nto\ndate\nand\nmodified\nas\nnecessary\n.\n4\n.\nThe\nnetwork\nstatement\nshall\nbe\npublished\nno\nless\nthan\nfour\nmonths\nin\nadvance\nof\nthe\ndeadline\nfor\nrequests\nfor\ninfrastructure\ncapacity\n.\nCHAPTER\nII\nINFRASTRUCTURE\nCHARGES\nArticle\n4\nEstablishing\n,\ndetermining\nand\ncollecting\ncharges\n1\n.\nMember\nStates\nshall\nestablish\na\ncharging\nframework\nwhile\nrespecting\nthe\nmanagement\nindependence\nlaid\ndown\nin\nArticle\n4\nof\nDirective\n91/440/EEC\n.\nSubject\nto\nthe\nsaid\ncondition\nof\nmanagement\nindependence\n,\nMember\nStates\nshall\nalso\nestablish\nspecific\ncharging\nrules\nor\ndelegate\nsuch\npowers\nto\nthe\ninfrastructure\nmanager\n.\nThe\ndetermination\nof\nthe\ncharge\nfor\nthe\nuse\nof\ninfrastructure\nand\nthe\ncollection\nof\nthis\ncharge\nshall\nbe\nperformed\nby\nthe\ninfrastructure\nmanager\n.\n2\n.\nWhere\nthe\ninfrastructure\nmanager\n,\nin\nits\nlegal\nform\n,\norganisation\nor\ndecision-making\nfunctions\n,\nis\nnot\nindependent\nof\nany\nrailway\nundertaking\n,\nthe\nfunctions\n,\ndescribed\nin\nthis\nchapter\n,\nother\nthan\ncollecting\nthe\ncharges\nshall\nbe\nperformed\nby\na\ncharging\nbody\nthat\nis\nindependent\nin\nits\nlegal\nform\n,\norganisation\nand\ndecision-making\nfrom\nany\nrailway\nundertaking\n.\n3\n.\nInfrastructure\nmanagers\nshall\ncooperate\nto\nachieve\nthe\nefficient\noperation\nof\ntrain\nservices\nwhich\ncross\nmore\nthan\none\ninfrastructure\nnetwork\n.\nThey\nshall\nin\nparticular\naim\nto\nguarantee\nthe\noptimum\ncompetitiveness\nof\ninternational\nrail\nfreight\nand\nensure\nthe\nefficient\nutilisation\nof\nthe\nTrans-European\nRail\nFreight\nNetwork\n.\nThey\nmay\nestablish\nsuch\njoint\norganisations\nas\nare\nappropriate\nto\nenable\nthis\nto\ntake\nplace\n.\nAny\ncooperation\nor\njoint\norganisation\nshall\nbe\nbound\nby\nthe\nrules\nset\nout\nin\nthis\nDirective\n.\n4\n.\nExcept\nwhere\nspecific\narrangements\nare\nmade\nunder\nArticle\n8\n(\n2\n)\n,\ninfrastructure\nmanagers\nshall\nensure\nthat\nthe\ncharging\nscheme\nin\nuse\nis\nbased\non\nthe\nsame\nprinciples\nover\nthe\nwhole\nof\ntheir\nnetwork\n.\n5\n.\nInfrastructure\nmanagers\nshall\nensure\nthat\nthe\napplication\nof\nthe\ncharging\nscheme\nresults\nin\nequivalent\nand\nnon-discriminatory\ncharges\nfor\ndifferent\nrailway\nundertakings\nthat\nperform\nservices\nof\nequivalent\nnature\nin\na\nsimilar\npart\nof\nthe\nmarket\nand\nthat\nthe\ncharges\nactually\napplied\ncomply\nwith\nthe\nrules\nlaid\ndown\nin\nthe\nnetwork\nstatement\n.\n6\n.\nAn\ninfrastructure\nmanager\nor\ncharging\nbody\nshall\nrespect\nthe\ncommercial\nconfidentiality\nof\ninformation\nprovided\nto\nit\nby\napplicants\n.\nArticle\n5\nServices\n1\n.\nRailway\nundertakings\nshall\n,\non\na\nnon-discriminatory\nbasis\n,\nbe\nentitled\nto\nthe\nminimum\naccess\npackage\nand\ntrack\naccess\nto\nservice\nfacilities\nthat\nare\ndescribed\nin\nAnnex\nII\n.\nThe\nsupply\nof\nservices\nreferred\nto\nin\nAnnex\nII\n,\npoint\n2\nshall\nbe\nprovided\nin\na\nnon-discriminatory\nmanner\nand\nrequests\nby\nrailway\nundertakings\nmay\nonly\nbe\nrejected\nif\nviable\nalternatives\nunder\nmarket\nconditions\nexist\n.\nIf\nthe\nservices\nare\nnot\noffered\nby\none\ninfrastructure\nmanager\n,\nthe\nprovider\nof\nthe\n``\nmain\ninfrastructure\n''\nshall\nuse\nall\nreasonable\nendeavours\nto\nfacilitate\nthe\nprovision\nof\nthese\nservices\n.\n2\n.\nWhere\nthe\ninfrastructure\nmanager\noffers\nany\nof\nthe\nrange\nof\nservices\ndescribed\nin\nAnnex\nII\n,\npoint\n3\nas\nadditional\nservices\nhe\nshall\nsupply\nthem\nupon\nrequest\nto\na\nrailway\nundertaking\n.\n3\n.\nRailway\nundertakings\nmay\nrequest\na\nfurther\nrange\nof\nancillary\nservices\n,\nlisted\nin\nAnnex\nII\n,\npoint\n4\nfrom\nthe\ninfrastructure\nmanager\nor\nfrom\nother\nsuppliers\n.\nThe\ninfrastructure\nmanager\nis\nnot\nobliged\nto\nsupply\nthese\nservices\n.\nArticle\n6\nInfrastructure\ncost\nand\naccounts\n1\n.\nMember\nStates\nshall\nlay\ndown\nconditions\n,\nincluding\nwhere\nappropriate\nadvance\npayments\n,\nto\nensure\nthat\n,\nunder\nnormal\nbusiness\nconditions\nand\nover\na\nreasonable\ntime\nperiod\n,\nthe\naccounts\nof\nan\ninfrastructure\nmanager\nshall\nat\nleast\nbalance\nincome\nfrom\ninfrastructure\ncharges\n,\nsurpluses\nfrom\nother\ncommercial\nactivities\nand\nState\nfunding\non\nthe\none\nhand\n,\nand\ninfrastructure\nexpenditure\non\nthe\nother\n.\nWithout\nprejudice\nto\nthe\npossible\nlong-term\naim\nof\nuser\ncover\nof\ninfrastructure\ncosts\nfor\nall\nmodes\nof\ntransport\non\nthe\nbasis\nof\nfair\n,\nnon-discriminatory\ncompetition\nbetween\nthe\nvarious\nmodes\n,\nwhere\nrail\ntransport\nis\nable\nto\ncompete\nwith\nother\nmodes\nof\ntransport\n,\nwithin\nthe\ncharging\nframework\nof\nArticles\n7\nand\n8\n,\na\nMember\nState\nmay\nrequire\nthe\ninfrastructure\nmanager\nto\nbalance\nhis\naccounts\nwithout\nState\nfunding\n.\n2\n.\nInfrastructure\nmanagers\nshall\n,\nwith\ndue\nregard\nto\nsafety\nand\nto\nmaintaining\nand\nimproving\nthe\nquality\nof\nthe\ninfrastructure\nservice\n,\nbe\nprovided\nwith\nincentives\nto\nreduce\nthe\ncosts\nof\nprovision\nof\ninfrastructure\nand\nthe\nlevel\nof\naccess\ncharges\n.\n3\n.\nMember\nStates\nshall\nensure\nthat\nthe\nprovision\nset\nout\nin\nparagraph\n2\nis\nimplemented\n,\neither\nthrough\na\ncontractual\nagreement\nbetween\nthe\ncompetent\nauthority\nand\ninfrastructure\nmanager\ncovering\na\nperiod\nof\nnot\nless\nthan\nthree\nyears\nwhich\nprovides\nfor\nState\nfunding\nor\nthrough\nthe\nestablishment\nof\nappropriate\nregulatory\nmeasures\nwith\nadequate\npowers\n.\n4\n.\nWhere\na\ncontractual\nagreement\nexists\n,\nthe\nterms\nof\nthe\ncontract\nand\nthe\nstructure\nof\nthe\npayments\nagreed\nto\nprovide\nfunding\nto\nthe\ninfrastructure\nmanager\nshall\nbe\nagreed\nin\nadvance\nto\ncover\nthe\nwhole\nof\nthe\ncontract\nperiod\n.\n5\n.\nA\nmethod\nfor\napportioning\ncosts\nshall\nbe\nestablished\n.\nMember\nStates\nmay\nrequire\nprior\napproval\n.\nThis\nmethod\nshould\nbe\nupdated\nfrom\ntime\nto\ntime\nto\nthe\nbest\ninternational\npractice\n.\nArticle\n7\nPrinciples\nof\ncharging\n1\n.\nCharges\nfor\nthe\nuse\nof\nrailway\ninfrastructure\nshall\nbe\npaid\nto\nthe\ninfrastructure\nmanager\nand\nused\nto\nfund\nhis\nbusiness\n.\n2\n.\nMember\nStates\nmay\nrequire\nthe\ninfrastructure\nmanager\nto\nprovide\nall\nnecessary\ninformation\non\nthe\ncharges\nimposed\n.\nThe\ninfrastructure\nmanager\nmust\n,\nin\nthis\nregard\n,\nbe\nable\nto\njustify\nthat\ninfrastructure\ncharges\nactually\ninvoiced\nto\neach\noperator\n,\npursuant\nto\nArticles\n4\nto\n12\n,\ncomply\nwith\nthe\nmethodology\n,\nrules\n,\nand\nwhere\napplicable\n,\nscales\nlaid\ndown\nin\nthe\nnetwork\nstatement\n.\n3\n.\nWithout\nprejudice\nto\nparagraphs\n4\nor\n5\nor\nto\nArticle\n8\n,\nthe\ncharges\nfor\nthe\nminimum\naccess\npackage\nand\ntrack\naccess\nto\nservice\nfacilities\nshall\nbe\nset\nat\nthe\ncost\nthat\nis\ndirectly\nincurred\nas\na\nresult\nof\noperating\nthe\ntrain\nservice\n.\n4\n.\nThe\ninfrastructure\ncharge\nmay\ninclude\na\ncharge\nwhich\nreflects\nthe\nscarcity\nof\ncapacity\nof\nthe\nidentifiable\nsegment\nof\nthe\ninfrastructure\nduring\nperiods\nof\ncongestion\n.\n5\n.\nThe\ninfrastructure\ncharge\nmay\nbe\nmodified\nto\ntake\naccount\nof\nthe\ncost\nof\nthe\nenvironmental\neffects\ncaused\nby\nthe\noperation\nof\nthe\ntrain\n.\nSuch\na\nmodification\nshall\nbe\ndifferentiated\naccording\nto\nthe\nmagnitude\nof\nthe\neffect\ncaused\n.\nCharging\nof\nenvironmental\ncosts\nwhich\nresults\nin\nan\nincrease\nin\nthe\noverall\nrevenue\naccruing\nto\nthe\ninfrastructure\nmanager\nshall\nhowever\nbe\nallowed\nonly\nif\nsuch\ncharging\nis\napplied\nat\na\ncomparable\nlevel\nto\ncompeting\nmodes\nof\ntransport\n.\nIn\nthe\nabsence\nof\nany\ncomparable\nlevel\nof\ncharging\nof\nenvironmental\ncosts\nin\nother\ncompeting\nmodes\nof\ntransport\n,\nsuch\nmodification\nshall\nnot\nresult\nin\nany\noverall\nchange\nin\nrevenue\nto\nthe\ninfrastructure\nmanager\n.\nIf\na\ncomparable\nlevel\nof\ncharging\nof\nenvironmental\ncosts\nhas\nbeen\nintroduced\nfor\nrail\nand\ncompeting\nmodes\nof\ntransport\nand\nthat\ngenerates\nadditional\nrevenue\n,\nit\nshall\nbe\nfor\nMember\nStates\nto\ndecide\nhow\nthe\nrevenue\nshall\nbe\nused\n.\n6\n.\nTo\navoid\nundesirable\ndisproportionate\nfluctuations\n,\nthe\ncharges\nreferred\nto\nin\nparagraphs\n3\n,\n4\nand\n5\nmay\nbe\naveraged\nover\na\nreasonable\nspread\nof\ntrain\nservices\nand\ntimes\n.\nNevertheless\n,\nthe\nrelative\nmagnitudes\nof\nthe\ninfrastructure\ncharges\nshall\nbe\nrelated\nto\nthe\ncosts\nattributable\nto\nthe\nservices\n.\n7\n.\nThe\nsupply\nof\nservices\nreferred\nto\nin\nAnnex\nII\n,\npoint\n2\n,\nshall\nnot\nbe\ncovered\nby\nthis\nArticle\n.\nWithout\nprejudice\nto\nthe\nforegoing\n,\naccount\nshall\nbe\ntaken\n,\nin\nsetting\nthe\nprices\nfor\nthe\nservices\nset\nout\nin\nAnnex\nII\n,\npoint\n2\n,\nof\nthe\ncompetitive\nsituation\nof\nrail\ntransport\n.\n8\n.\nWhere\nservices\nlisted\nin\nAnnex\nII\n,\npoints\n3\nand\n4\nas\nadditional\nand\nancillary\nservices\nare\noffered\nonly\nby\none\nsupplier\nthe\ncharge\nimposed\nfor\nsuch\na\nservice\nshall\nrelate\nto\nthe\ncost\nof\nproviding\nit\n,\ncalculated\non\nthe\nbasis\nof\nthe\nactual\nlevel\nof\nuse\n.\n9\n.\nCharges\nmay\nbe\nlevied\nfor\ncapacity\nused\nfor\nthe\npurpose\nof\ninfrastructure\nmaintenance\n.\nSuch\ncharges\nshall\nnot\nexceed\nthe\nnet\nrevenue\nloss\nto\nthe\ninfrastructure\nmanager\ncaused\nby\nthe\nmaintenance\n.\nArticle\n8\nExceptions\nto\ncharging\nprinciples\n1\n.\nIn\norder\nto\nobtain\nfull\nrecovery\nof\nthe\ncosts\nincurred\nby\nthe\ninfrastructure\nmanager\na\nMember\nState\nmay\n,\nif\nthe\nmarket\ncan\nbear\nthis\n,\nlevy\nmark-ups\non\nthe\nbasis\nof\nefficient\n,\ntransparent\nand\nnon-discriminatory\nprinciples\n,\nwhile\nguaranteeing\noptimum\ncompetitiveness\nin\nparticular\nof\ninternational\nrail\nfreight\n.\nThe\ncharging\nsystem\nshall\nrespect\nthe\nproductivity\nincreases\nachieved\nby\nrailway\nundertakings\n.\nThe\nlevel\nof\ncharges\nmust\nnot\n,\nhowever\n,\nexclude\nthe\nuse\nof\ninfrastructure\nby\nmarket\nsegments\nwhich\ncan\npay\nat\nleast\nthe\ncost\nthat\nis\ndirectly\nincurred\nas\na\nresult\nof\noperating\nthe\nrailway\nservice\n,\nplus\na\nrate\nof\nreturn\nwhich\nthe\nmarket\ncan\nbear\n.\n2\n.\nFor\nspecific\ninvestment\nprojects\n,\nin\nthe\nfuture\n,\nor\nthat\nhave\nbeen\ncompleted\nnot\nmore\nthan\n15\nyears\nbefore\nthe\nentry\ninto\nforce\nof\nthis\nDirective\n,\nthe\ninfrastructure\nmanager\nmay\nset\nor\ncontinue\nto\nset\nhigher\ncharges\non\nthe\nbasis\nof\nthe\nlong-term\ncosts\nof\nsuch\nprojects\nif\nthey\nincrease\nefficiency\nand/or\ncost-effectiveness\nand\ncould\nnot\notherwise\nbe\nor\nhave\nbeen\nundertaken\n.\nSuch\na\ncharging\narrangement\nmay\nalso\nincorporate\nagreements\non\nthe\nsharing\nof\nthe\nrisk\nassociated\nwith\nnew\ninvestments\n.\n3\n.\nTo\nprevent\ndiscrimination\n,\nit\nshall\nbe\nensured\nthat\nany\ngiven\ninfrastructure\nmanager\n's\naverage\nand\nmarginal\ncharges\nfor\nequivalent\nuses\nof\nhis\ninfrastructure\nare\ncomparable\nand\nthat\ncomparable\nservices\nin\nthe\nsame\nmarket\nsegment\nare\nsubject\nto\nthe\nsame\ncharges\n.\nThe\ninfrastructure\nmanager\nshall\nshow\nin\nthe\nnetwork\nstatement\nthat\nthe\ncharging\nsystem\nmeets\nthese\nrequirements\nin\nso\nfar\nas\nthis\ncan\nbe\ndone\nwithout\ndisclosing\nconfidential\nbusiness\ninformation\n.\n4\n.\nIf\nan\ninfrastructure\nmanager\nintends\nto\nmodify\nthe\nessential\nelements\nof\nthe\ncharging\nsystem\nreferred\nto\nin\nparagraph\n1\n,\nit\nshall\nmake\nthem\npublic\nat\nleast\nthree\nmonths\nin\nadvance\n.\nArticle\n9\nDiscounts\n1\n.\nWithout\nprejudice\nto\nArticles\n81\n,\n82\n,\n86\nand\n87\nof\nthe\nTreaty\nand\nnotwithstanding\nArticle\n7\n(\n3\n)\nof\nthis\nDirective\n,\nany\ndiscount\non\nthe\ncharges\nlevied\non\na\nrailway\nundertaking\nby\nthe\ninfrastructure\nmanager\n,\nfor\nany\nservice\n,\nshall\ncomply\nwith\nthe\ncriteria\nset\nout\nin\nthis\nArticle\n.\n2\n.\nWith\nthe\nexception\nof\nparagraph\n3\n,\ndiscounts\nshall\nbe\nlimited\nto\nthe\nactual\nsaving\nof\nthe\nadministrative\ncost\nto\nthe\ninfrastructure\nmanager\n.\nIn\ndetermining\nthe\nlevel\nof\ndiscount\n,\nno\naccount\nmay\nbe\ntaken\nof\ncost\nsavings\nalready\ninternalised\nin\nthe\ncharge\nlevied\n.\n3\n.\nInfrastructure\nmanagers\nmay\nintroduce\nschemes\navailable\nto\nall\nusers\nof\nthe\ninfrastructure\n,\nfor\nspecified\ntraffic\nflows\n,\ngranting\ntime\nlimited\ndiscounts\nto\nencourage\nthe\ndevelopment\nof\nnew\nrail\nservices\n,\nor\ndiscounts\nencouraging\nthe\nuse\nof\nconsiderably\nunderutilised\nlines\n.\n4\n.\nDiscounts\nmay\nrelate\nonly\nto\ncharges\nlevied\nfor\na\nspecified\ninfrastructure\nsection\n.\n5\n.\nSimilar\ndiscount\nschemes\nshall\napply\nfor\nsimilar\nservices\n.\nArticle\n10\nCompensation\nschemes\nfor\nunpaid\nenvironmental\n,\naccident\nand\ninfrastructure\ncosts\n1\n.\nMember\nStates\nmay\nput\nin\nplace\na\ntime-limited\ncompensation\nscheme\nfor\nthe\nuse\nof\nrailway\ninfrastructure\nfor\nthe\ndemonstrably\nunpaid\nenvironmental\n,\naccident\nand\ninfrastructure\ncosts\nof\ncompeting\ntransport\nmodes\nin\nso\nfar\nas\nthese\ncosts\nexceed\nthe\nequivalent\ncosts\nof\nrail\n.\n2\n.\nWhere\nan\noperator\nreceiving\ncompensation\nenjoys\nan\nexclusive\nright\n,\nthe\ncompensation\nmust\nbe\naccompanied\nby\ncomparable\nbenefits\nto\nusers\n.\n3\n.\nThe\nmethodology\nused\nand\ncalculations\nperformed\nmust\nbe\npublicly\navailable\n.\nIt\nshall\nin\nparticular\nbe\npossible\nto\ndemonstrate\nthe\nspecific\nuncharged\ncosts\nof\nthe\ncompeting\ntransport\ninfrastructure\nthat\nare\navoided\nand\nto\nensure\nthat\nthe\nscheme\nis\ngranted\non\nnon-discriminatory\nterms\nto\nundertakings\n.\n4\n.\nMember\nStates\nshall\nensure\nthat\nsuch\na\nscheme\nis\ncompatible\nwith\nArticles\n73\n,\n87\nand\n88\nof\nthe\nTreaty\n.\nArticle\n11\nPerformance\nscheme\n1\n.\nInfrastructure\ncharging\nschemes\nshall\nthrough\na\nperformance\nscheme\nencourage\nrailway\nundertakings\nand\nthe\ninfrastructure\nmanager\nto\nminimise\ndisruption\nand\nimprove\nthe\nperformance\nof\nthe\nrailway\nnetwork\n.\nThis\nmay\ninclude\npenalties\nfor\nactions\nwhich\ndisrupt\nthe\noperation\nof\nthe\nnetwork\n,\ncompensation\nfor\nundertakings\nwhich\nsuffer\nfrom\ndisruption\nand\nbonuses\nthat\nreward\nbetter\nthan\nplanned\nperformance\n.\n2\n.\nThe\nbasic\nprinciples\nof\nthe\nperformance\nscheme\nshall\napply\nthroughout\nthe\nnetwork\n.\nArticle\n12\nReservation\ncharges\nInfrastructure\nmanagers\nmay\nlevy\nan\nappropriate\ncharge\nfor\ncapacity\nthat\nis\nrequested\nbut\nnot\nused\n.\nThis\ncharge\nshall\nprovide\nincentives\nfor\nefficient\nuse\nof\ncapacity\n.\nThe\ninfrastructure\nmanager\nshall\nalways\nbe\nable\nto\ninform\nany\ninterested\nparty\nof\nthe\ninfrastructure\ncapacity\nwhich\nhas\nbeen\nallocated\nto\nuser\nrailway\nundertakings\n.\nCHAPTER\nIII\nALLOCATION\nOF\nINFRASTRUCTURE\nCAPACITY\nArticle\n13\nCapacity\nrights\n1\n.\nInfrastructure\ncapacity\nshall\nbe\nallocated\nby\nan\ninfrastructure\nmanager\n,\nand\nonce\nallocated\nto\nan\napplicant\nmay\nnot\nbe\ntransferred\nby\nthe\nrecipient\nto\nanother\nundertaking\nor\nservice\n.\nAny\ntrading\nin\ninfrastructure\ncapacity\nshall\nbe\nprohibited\nand\nshall\nlead\nto\nexclusion\nfrom\nthe\nfurther\nallocation\nof\ncapacity\n.\nThe\nuse\nof\ncapacity\nby\na\nrailway\nundertaking\nwhen\ncarrying\nout\nthe\nbusiness\nof\nan\napplicant\nwho\nis\nnot\na\nrailway\nundertaking\nshall\nnot\nbe\nconsidered\na\ntransfer\n.\n2\n.\nThe\nright\nto\nuse\nspecific\ninfrastructure\ncapacity\nin\nthe\nform\nof\na\ntrain\npath\nmay\nbe\ngranted\nto\napplicants\nfor\na\nmaximum\nduration\nof\none\nworking\ntimetable\nperiod\n.\nAn\ninfrastructure\nmanager\nand\nan\napplicant\nmay\nenter\ninto\na\nframework\nagreement\nas\nlaid\ndown\nin\nArticle\n17\nfor\nthe\nuse\nof\ncapacity\non\nthe\nrelevant\nrailway\ninfrastructure\nfor\na\nlonger\nterm\nthan\none\nworking\ntimetable\nperiod\n.\n3\n.\nThe\ndefinition\nof\nrespective\nrights\nand\nobligations\nbetween\ninfrastructure\nmanagers\nand\napplicants\nin\nrespect\nof\nany\nallocation\nof\ncapacity\nshall\nbe\nlaid\ndown\nin\ncontracts\nor\nlegislation\n.\nArticle\n14\nCapacity\nallocation\n1\n.\nMember\nStates\nmay\nestablish\na\nframework\nfor\nthe\nallocation\nof\ninfrastructure\ncapacity\nwhile\nrespecting\nthe\nmanagement\nindependence\nlaid\ndown\nin\nArticle\n4\nof\nDirective\n91/440/EEC\n.\nSpecific\ncapacity\nallocation\nrules\nshall\nbe\nestablished\n.\nThe\ninfrastructure\nmanager\nshall\nperform\nthe\ncapacity\nallocation\nprocesses\n.\nIn\nparticular\n,\nthe\ninfrastructure\nmanager\nshall\nensure\nthat\ninfrastructure\ncapacity\nis\nallocated\non\na\nfair\nand\nnon-discriminatory\nbasis\nand\nin\naccordance\nwith\nCommunity\nlaw\n.\n2\n.\nWhere\nthe\ninfrastructure\nmanager\n,\nin\nits\nlegal\nform\n,\norganisation\nor\ndecision-making\nfunctions\nis\nnot\nindependent\nof\nany\nrailway\nundertaking\n,\nthe\nfunctions\nreferred\nto\nin\nparagraph\n1\nand\ndescribed\nin\nthis\nchapter\nshall\nbe\nperformed\nby\nan\nallocation\nbody\nthat\nis\nindependent\nin\nits\nlegal\nform\n,\norganisation\nand\ndecision-making\nfrom\nany\nrailway\nundertaking\n.\n3\n.\nInfrastructure\nmanagers\nand\nallocation\nbodies\nshall\nrespect\nthe\ncommercial\nconfidentiality\nof\ninformation\nprovided\nto\nthem\n.\nArticle\n15\nCooperation\nin\nthe\nallocation\nof\ninfrastructure\ncapacity\non\nmore\nthan\none\nnetwork\n1\n.\nInfrastructure\nmanagers\nshall\ncooperate\nto\nenable\nthe\nefficient\ncreation\nand\nallocation\nof\ninfrastructure\ncapacity\nwhich\ncrosses\nmore\nthan\none\nnetwork\n.\nThey\nshall\norganise\ninternational\ntrain\npaths\n,\nin\nparticular\nwithin\nthe\nframework\nof\nthe\nTrans-European\nRail\nFreight\nNetwork\n.\nThey\nshall\nestablish\nsuch\nprocedures\nas\nare\nappropriate\nto\nenable\nthis\nto\ntake\nplace\n.\nThese\nprocedures\nshall\nbe\nbound\nby\nthe\nrules\nset\nout\nin\nthis\nDirective\n.\nThe\nprocedure\nestablished\nin\norder\nto\ncoordinate\nthe\nallocation\nof\ninfrastructure\ncapacity\nat\nan\ninternational\nlevel\nshall\nassociate\nrepresentatives\nof\ninfrastructure\nmanagers\nfor\nall\nrailway\ninfrastructures\nwhose\nallocation\ndecisions\nhave\nan\nimpact\non\nmore\nthan\none\nother\ninfrastructure\nmanager\n.\nAppropriate\nrepresentatives\nof\ninfrastructure\nmanagers\nfrom\noutside\nthe\nCommunity\nmay\nbe\nassociated\nwith\nthese\nprocedures\n.\nThe\nCommission\nshall\nbe\ninformed\nand\ninvited\nto\nattend\nas\nan\nobserver\n.\n2\n.\nAt\nany\nmeeting\nor\nother\nactivity\nundertaken\nto\npermit\nthe\nallocation\nof\ninfrastructure\ncapacity\nfor\ntrans-network\ntrain\nservices\n,\ndecisions\nshall\nonly\nbe\ntaken\nby\nrepresentatives\nof\ninfrastructure\nmanagers\n.\n3\n.\nThe\nparticipants\nin\nthe\ncooperation\nreferred\nto\nparagraph\n1\nshall\nensure\nthat\nits\nmembership\n,\nmethods\nof\noperation\nand\nall\nrelevant\ncriteria\nwhich\nare\nused\nfor\nassessing\nand\nallocating\ninfrastructure\ncapacity\nbe\nmade\npublicly\navailable\n.\n4\n.\nWorking\nin\ncooperation\nas\nreferred\nto\nin\nparagraph\n1\n,\ninfrastructure\nmanagers\nshall\nassess\nthe\nneed\nfor\n,\nand\nmay\nwhere\nnecessary\npropose\nand\norganise\ninternational\ntrain\npaths\nto\nfacilitate\nthe\noperation\nof\nfreight\ntrains\nwhich\nare\nsubject\nto\nan\nad\nhoc\nrequest\nas\nreferred\nto\nin\nArticle\n23\n.\nSuch\nprearranged\ninternational\ntrain\npaths\nshall\nbe\nmade\navailable\nto\napplicants\nvia\nany\nof\nthe\nparticipating\ninfrastructure\nmanagers\n.\nArticle\n16\nApplicants\n1\n.\nApplications\nfor\ninfrastructure\ncapacity\nmay\nbe\nmade\nby\nrailway\nundertakings\nand\ntheir\ninternational\ngroupings\nand\n,\nin\nthe\nterritories\nof\nthose\nMember\nStates\nwhich\nso\nallow\n,\nby\nother\napplicants\ncomplying\nwith\nthe\ndefinition\nin\nArticle\n2\n(\nb\n)\n.\nMember\nStates\nmay\nalso\nallow\nother\napplicants\nto\napply\nfor\ninfrastructure\ncapacity\non\ntheir\nterritories\n.\n2\n.\nThe\ninfrastructure\nmanager\nmay\nset\nrequirements\nwith\nregard\nto\napplicants\nto\nensure\nthat\nits\nlegitimate\nexpectations\nabout\nfuture\nrevenues\nand\nutilisation\nof\nthe\ninfrastructure\nare\nsafeguarded\n.\nSuch\nrequirements\nshall\nbe\nappropriate\n,\ntransparent\nand\nnon-discriminatory\n.\nThe\nrequirements\nshall\nbe\npublished\nas\npart\nof\nthe\nallocation\nprinciples\nin\nthe\nnetwork\nstatement\n,\nand\nthe\nCommission\nshall\nbe\ninformed\n.\n3\n.\nThe\nrequirements\nin\nparagraph\n2\nmay\nonly\ninclude\nthe\nprovision\nof\na\nfinancial\nguarantee\nthat\nmust\nnot\nexceed\nan\nappropriate\nlevel\nwhich\nshall\nbe\nproportional\nto\nthe\ncontemplated\nlevel\nof\nactivity\nof\nthe\napplicant\n,\nand\nassurance\nof\nthe\ncapability\nto\nprepare\ncompliant\nbids\nfor\ninfrastructure\ncapacity\n.\nArticle\n17\nFramework\nagreements\n1\n.\nWithout\nprejudice\nto\nArticles\n81\n,\n82\nand\n86\nof\nthe\nTreaty\n,\na\nframework\nagreement\nmay\nbe\nconcluded\nwith\nan\napplicant\n.\nSuch\na\nframework\nagreement\nspecifies\nthe\ncharacteristics\nof\nthe\ninfrastructure\ncapacity\nrequired\nby\nand\noffered\nto\nthe\napplicant\nover\na\nperiod\nof\ntime\nexceeding\none\nworking\ntimetable\nperiod\n.\nThe\nframework\nagreement\nshall\nnot\nspecify\na\ntrain\npath\nin\ndetail\n,\nbut\nshould\nbe\nsuch\nas\nto\nseek\nto\nmeet\nthe\nlegitimate\ncommercial\nneeds\nof\nthe\napplicant\n.\nA\nMember\nState\nmay\nrequire\nprior\napproval\nof\nsuch\na\nframework\nagreement\nby\nthe\nregulatory\nbody\nreferred\nto\nin\nArticle\n30\nof\nthis\nDirective\n.\n2\n.\nFramework\nagreements\nshall\nnot\nbe\nsuch\nas\nto\npreclude\nthe\nuse\nof\nthe\nrelevant\ninfrastructure\nby\nother\napplicants\nor\nservices\n.\n3\n.\nA\nframework\nagreement\nshall\nallow\nfor\nthe\namendment\nor\nlimitation\nof\nits\nterms\nto\nenable\nbetter\nuse\nto\nbe\nmade\nof\nthe\nrailway\ninfrastructure\n.\n4\n.\nThe\nframework\nagreement\nmay\ncontain\npenalties\nshould\nit\nbe\nnecessary\nto\nmodify\nor\nterminate\nthe\nagreement\n.\n5\n.\nFramework\nagreements\nshall\nin\nprinciple\nbe\nfor\na\nperiod\nof\nfive\nyears\n.\nThe\ninfrastructure\nmanager\nmay\nagree\nto\na\nshorter\nor\nlonger\nperiod\nin\nspecific\ncases\n.\nAny\nperiod\nlonger\nthan\nfive\nyears\nshall\nbe\njustified\nby\nthe\nexistence\nof\ncommercial\ncontracts\n,\nspecialised\ninvestments\nor\nrisks\n.\nAny\nperiod\nlonger\nthan\n10\nyears\nshall\nbe\npossible\nonly\nin\nexceptional\ncases\n,\nin\nparticular\n,\nwhere\nthere\nis\nlarge-scale\n,\nlong-term\ninvestment\n,\nand\nparticularly\nwhere\nsuch\ninvestment\nis\ncovered\nby\ncontractual\ncommitments\n.\n6\n.\nWhile\nrespecting\ncommercial\nconfidentiality\n,\nthe\ngeneral\nnature\nof\neach\nframework\nagreement\nshall\nbe\nmade\navailable\nto\nany\ninterested\nparty\n.\nArticle\n18\nSchedule\nfor\nthe\nallocation\nprocess\n1\n.\nThe\ninfrastructure\nmanager\nshall\nadhere\nto\nthe\nschedule\nfor\ncapacity\nallocation\nset\nout\nin\nAnnex\nIII\n.\n2\n.\nInfrastructure\nmanagers\nshall\nagree\nwith\nthe\nother\nrelevant\ninfrastructure\nmanagers\nconcerned\nwhich\ninternational\ntrain\npaths\nare\nto\nbe\nincluded\nin\nthe\nworking\ntimetable\n,\nbefore\ncommencing\nconsultation\non\nthe\ndraft\nworking\ntimetable\n.\nAdjustments\nshall\nonly\nbe\nmade\nif\nabsolutely\nnecessary\n.\nArticle\n19\nApplication\n1\n.\nApplicants\nmay\napply\non\nthe\nbasis\nof\npublic\nor\nprivate\nlaw\nto\nthe\ninfrastructure\nmanager\nto\nrequest\nan\nagreement\ngranting\nrights\nto\nuse\nrailway\ninfrastructure\nagainst\na\ncharge\nas\nprovided\nfor\nin\nchapter\nII\n.\n2\n.\nRequests\nrelating\nto\nthe\nregular\nworking\ntimetable\nmust\nadhere\nto\nthe\ndeadlines\nset\nout\nin\nAnnex\nIII\n.\n3\n.\nAn\napplicant\nwho\nis\na\nparty\nto\na\nframework\nagreement\nshall\napply\nin\naccordance\nwith\nthat\nagreement\n.\n4\n.\nApplicants\nmay\nrequest\ninfrastructure\ncapacity\ncrossing\nmore\nthan\none\nnetwork\nby\napplying\nto\none\ninfrastructure\nmanager\n.\nThat\ninfrastructure\nmanager\nshall\nthen\nbe\npermitted\nto\nact\non\nbehalf\nof\nthe\napplicant\nto\nseek\ncapacity\nwith\nthe\nother\nrelevant\ninfrastructure\nmanagers\n.\n5\n.\nInfrastructure\nmanagers\nshall\nensure\nthat\n,\nfor\ninfrastructure\ncapacity\ncrossing\nmore\nthan\none\nnetwork\n,\napplicants\nmay\napply\ndirect\nto\nany\njoint\nbody\nwhich\nthe\ninfrastructure\nmanagers\nmay\nestablish\n.\nArticle\n20\nScheduling\n1\n.\nThe\ninfrastructure\nmanager\nshall\nas\nfar\nas\nis\npossible\nmeet\nall\nrequests\nfor\ninfrastructure\ncapacity\nincluding\nrequests\nfor\ntrain\npaths\ncrossing\nmore\nthan\none\nnetwork\n,\nand\nshall\nas\nfar\nas\npossible\ntake\naccount\nof\nall\nconstraints\non\napplicants\n,\nincluding\nthe\neconomic\neffect\non\ntheir\nbusiness\n.\n2\n.\nThe\ninfrastructure\nmanager\nmay\ngive\npriority\nto\nspecific\nservices\nwithin\nthe\nscheduling\nand\ncoordination\nprocess\nbut\nonly\nas\nset\nout\nin\nArticles\n22\nand\n24\n.\n3\n.\nThe\ninfrastructure\nmanager\nshall\nconsult\ninterested\nparties\nabout\nthe\ndraft\nworking\ntimetable\nand\nallow\nthem\nat\nleast\none\nmonth\nto\npresent\ntheir\nviews\n.\nInterested\nparties\nshall\ninclude\nall\nthose\nwho\nhave\nrequested\ninfrastructure\ncapacity\nas\nwell\nas\nother\nparties\nwho\nwish\nto\nhave\nthe\nopportunity\nto\ncomment\non\nhow\nthe\nworking\ntimetable\nmay\naffect\ntheir\nability\nto\nprocure\nrail\nservices\nduring\nthe\nworking\ntimetable\nperiod\n.\n4\n.\nThe\ninfrastructure\nmanager\nshall\ntake\nappropriate\nmeasures\nto\ndeal\nwith\nany\nconcerns\nthat\nare\nexpressed\n.\nArticle\n21\nCoordination\nprocess\n1\n.\nDuring\nthe\nscheduling\nprocess\nreferred\nto\nin\nArticle\n20\n,\nwhen\nthe\ninfrastructure\nmanager\nencounters\nconflicts\nbetween\ndifferent\nrequests\nhe\nshall\nattempt\n,\nthrough\ncoordination\nof\nthe\nrequests\n,\nto\nensure\nthe\nbest\npossible\nmatching\nof\nall\nrequirements\n.\n2\n.\nWhen\na\nsituation\nrequiring\ncoordination\narises\n,\nthe\ninfrastructure\nmanager\nshall\nhave\nthe\nright\n,\nwithin\nreasonable\nlimits\n,\nto\npropose\ninfrastructure\ncapacity\nthat\ndiffers\nfrom\nthat\nwhich\nwas\nrequested\n.\n3\n.\nThe\ninfrastructure\nmanager\nshall\nattempt\n,\nthrough\nconsultation\nwith\nthe\nappropriate\napplicants\n,\nto\nachieve\na\nresolution\nof\nany\nconflicts\n.\n4\n.\nThe\nprinciples\ngoverning\nthe\ncoordination\nprocess\nshall\nbe\ndefined\nin\nthe\nnetwork\nstatement\n.\nThese\nshall\nin\nparticular\nreflect\nthe\ndifficulty\nof\narranging\ninternational\ntrain\npaths\nand\nthe\neffect\nthat\nmodification\nmay\nhave\non\nother\ninfrastructure\nmanagers\n.\n5\n.\nWhen\nrequests\nfor\ninfrastructure\ncapacity\ncan\nnot\nbe\nsatisfied\nwithout\ncoordination\n,\nthe\ninfrastructure\nmanager\nshall\nattempt\nto\naccommodate\nall\nrequests\nthrough\ncoordination\n.\n6\n.\nWithout\nprejudice\nto\nthe\nexisting\nappeal\nprocedures\nand\nto\nthe\nprovisions\nof\nArticle\n30\n,\nin\ncase\nof\ndisputes\nrelating\nto\nthe\nallocation\nof\ninfrastructure\ncapacity\n,\na\ndispute\nresolution\nsystem\nshall\nbe\nmade\navailable\nin\norder\nto\nresolve\nsuch\ndisputes\npromptly\n.\nIf\nthis\nsystem\nis\napplied\n,\na\ndecision\nshall\nbe\nreached\nwithin\na\ntime\nlimit\nof\n10\nworking\ndays\n.\nArticle\n22\nCongested\ninfrastructure\n1\n.\nWhere\nafter\ncoordination\nof\nthe\nrequested\npaths\nand\nconsultation\nwith\napplicants\nit\nis\nnot\npossible\nto\nsatisfy\nrequests\nfor\ninfrastructure\ncapacity\nadequately\nthen\nthe\ninfrastructure\nmanager\nmust\nimmediately\ndeclare\nthat\nelement\nof\ninfrastructure\non\nwhich\nthis\nhas\noccurred\nto\nbe\ncongested\n.\nThis\nshall\nalso\nbe\ndone\nfor\ninfrastructure\nwhich\nit\ncan\nbe\nforeseen\nwill\nsuffer\nfrom\ninsufficient\ncapacity\nin\nthe\nnear\nfuture\n.\n2\n.\nWhen\ninfrastructure\nhas\nbeen\ndeclared\nto\nbe\ncongested\n,\nthe\ninfrastructure\nmanager\nshall\ncarry\nout\na\ncapacity\nanalysis\nas\ndescribed\nin\nArticle\n25\n,\nunless\na\ncapacity\nenhancement\nplan\nas\ndescribed\nin\nArticle\n26\nis\nalready\nbeing\nimplemented\n.\n3\n.\nWhen\ncharges\nin\naccordance\nwith\nArticle\n7\n(\n4\n)\nhave\nnot\nbeen\nlevied\nor\nhave\nnot\nachieved\na\nsatisfactory\nresult\nand\nthe\ninfrastructure\nhas\nbeen\ndeclared\nto\nbe\ncongested\n,\nthe\ninfrastructure\nmanager\nmay\nin\naddition\nemploy\npriority\ncriteria\nto\nallocate\ninfrastructure\ncapacity\n.\n4\n.\nThe\npriority\ncriteria\nshall\ntake\naccount\nof\nthe\nimportance\nof\na\nservice\nto\nsociety\n,\nrelative\nto\nany\nother\nservice\nwhich\nwill\nconsequently\nbe\nexcluded\n.\nIn\norder\nto\nguarantee\nwithin\nthis\nframework\nthe\ndevelopment\nof\nadequate\ntransport\nservices\n,\nin\nparticular\nto\ncomply\nwith\npublic-service\nrequirements\nor\npromote\nthe\ndevelopment\nof\nrail\nfreight\n,\nMember\nStates\nmay\ntake\nany\nmeasures\nnecessary\n,\nunder\nnon-discriminatory\nconditions\n,\nto\nensure\nthat\nsuch\nservices\nare\ngiven\npriority\nwhen\ninfrastructure\ncapacity\nis\nallocated\n.\nMember\nStates\nmay\n,\nwhere\nappropriate\n,\ngrant\nthe\ninfrastructure\nmanager\ncompensation\ncorresponding\nto\nany\nloss\nof\nrevenue\nrelated\nto\nthe\nneed\nto\nallocate\na\ngiven\ncapacity\nto\ncertain\nservices\npursuant\nto\nthe\nprevious\nsubparagraph\n.\nThis\nshall\ninclude\ntaking\naccount\nof\nthe\neffect\nof\nthis\nexclusion\nin\nother\nMember\nStates\n.\n5\n.\nThe\nimportance\nof\nfreight\nservices\nand\nin\nparticular\ninternational\nfreight\nservices\nshall\nbe\ngiven\nadequate\nconsideration\nin\ndetermining\npriority\ncriteria\n.\n6\n.\nThe\nprocedures\nwhich\nshall\nbe\nfollowed\nand\ncriteria\nused\nwhere\ninfrastructure\nis\ncongested\nshall\nbe\nset\nout\nin\nthe\nnetwork\nstatement\n.\nArticle\n23\nAd\nhoc\nrequests\n1\n.\nThe\ninfrastructure\nmanager\nshall\nrespond\nto\nad\nhoc\nrequests\nfor\nindividual\ntrain\npaths\nas\nquickly\nas\npossible\n,\nand\nin\nany\nevent\n,\nwithin\nfive\nworking\ndays\n.\nInformation\nsupplied\non\navailable\nspare\ncapacity\nshall\nbe\nmade\navailable\nto\nall\napplicants\nwho\nmay\nwish\nto\nuse\nthis\ncapacity\n.\n2\n.\nInfrastructure\nmanagers\nshall\nwhere\nnecessary\nundertake\nan\nevaluation\nof\nthe\nneed\nfor\nreserve\ncapacity\nto\nbe\nkept\navailable\nwithin\nthe\nfinal\nscheduled\nworking\ntimetable\nto\nenable\nthem\nto\nrespond\nrapidly\nto\nforeseeable\nad\nhoc\nrequests\nfor\ncapacity\n.\nThis\nshall\nalso\napply\nin\ncases\nof\ncongested\ninfrastructure\n.\nArticle\n24\nSpecialised\ninfrastructure\n1\n.\nWithout\nprejudice\nto\nparagraph\n2\n,\ninfrastructure\ncapacity\nshall\nbe\nconsidered\nto\nbe\navailable\nfor\nthe\nuse\nof\nall\ntypes\nof\nservice\nwhich\nconform\nto\nthe\ncharacteristics\nnecessary\nfor\noperation\non\nthe\ntrain\npath\n.\n2\n.\nWhere\nthere\nare\nsuitable\nalternative\nroutes\n,\nthe\ninfrastructure\nmanager\nmay\n,\nafter\nconsultation\nwith\ninterested\nparties\n,\ndesignate\nparticular\ninfrastructure\nfor\nuse\nby\nspecified\ntypes\nof\ntraffic\n.\nWithout\nprejudice\nto\nArticles\n81\n,\n82\nand\n86\nof\nthe\nTreaty\n,\nwhen\nsuch\ndesignation\nhas\noccurred\n,\nthe\ninfrastructure\nmanager\nmay\ngive\npriority\nto\nthis\ntype\nof\ntraffic\nwhen\nallocating\ninfrastructure\ncapacity\n.\nSuch\ndesignation\nshall\nnot\nprevent\nthe\nuse\nof\nsuch\ninfrastructure\nby\nother\ntypes\nof\ntraffic\nwhen\ncapacity\nis\navailable\nand\nwhen\nthe\nrolling\nstock\nconforms\nto\nthe\ntechnical\ncharacteristics\nnecessary\nfor\noperation\non\nthe\nline\n.\n3\n.\nWhen\ninfrastructure\nhas\nbeen\ndesignated\npursuant\nto\nparagraph\n2\n,\nthis\nshall\nbe\ndescribed\nin\nthe\nnetwork\nstatement\n.\nArticle\n25\nCapacity\nanalysis\n1\n.\nThe\nobjective\nof\ncapacity\nanalysis\nis\nto\ndetermine\nthe\nrestrictions\non\ninfrastructure\ncapacity\nwhich\nprevent\nrequests\nfor\ncapacity\nfrom\nbeing\nadequately\nmet\n,\nand\nto\npropose\nmethods\nof\nenabling\nadditional\nrequests\nto\nbe\nsatisfied\n.\nThis\nanalysis\nshall\nidentify\nthe\nreasons\nfor\nthe\ncongestion\nand\nwhat\nmeasures\nmight\nbe\ntaken\nin\nthe\nshort\nand\nmedium\nterm\nto\nease\nthe\ncongestion\n.\n2\n.\nThe\nanalysis\nshall\nconsider\nthe\ninfrastructure\n,\nthe\noperating\nprocedures\n,\nthe\nnature\nof\nthe\ndifferent\nservices\noperating\nand\nthe\neffect\nof\nall\nthese\nfactors\non\ninfrastructure\ncapacity\n.\nMeasures\nto\nbe\nconsidered\nshall\ninclude\nin\nparticular\nre-routing\nof\nservices\n,\nre-timing\nservices\n,\nspeed\nalterations\nand\ninfrastructure\nimprovements\n.\n3\n.\nA\ncapacity\nanalysis\nshall\nbe\ncompleted\nwithin\nsix\nmonths\nof\nthe\nidentification\nof\ninfrastructure\nas\ncongested\n.\nArticle\n26\nCapacity\nenhancement\nplan\n1\n.\nWithin\nsix\nmonths\nof\nthe\ncompletion\nof\na\ncapacity\nanalysis\n,\nthe\ninfrastructure\nmanager\nshall\nproduce\na\ncapacity\nenhancement\nplan\n.\n2\n.\nA\ncapacity\nenhancement\nplan\nshall\nbe\ndeveloped\nafter\nconsultation\nwith\nusers\nof\nthe\nrelevant\ncongested\ninfrastructure\n.\nIt\nshall\nidentify\n:\na\n)\nthe\nreasons\nfor\nthe\ncongestion\n;\nb\n)\nthe\nlikely\nfuture\ndevelopment\nof\ntraffic\n;\nc\n)\nthe\nconstraints\non\ninfrastructure\ndevelopment\n;\nd\n)\nthe\noptions\nand\ncosts\nfor\ncapacity\nenhancement\n,\nincluding\nlikely\nchanges\nto\naccess\ncharges\n.\nIt\nshall\nalso\n,\non\nthe\nbasis\nof\na\ncost\nbenefit\nanalysis\nof\nthe\npossible\nmeasures\nidentified\n,\ndetermine\nwhat\naction\nshall\nbe\ntaken\nto\nenhance\ninfrastructure\ncapacity\n,\nincluding\na\ncalendar\nfor\nimplementation\nof\nthe\nmeasures\n.\nThe\nplan\nmay\nbe\nsubject\nto\nprior\napproval\nby\nthe\nMember\nState\n.\n3\n.\nThe\ninfrastructure\nmanager\nshall\ncease\nto\nlevy\nany\nfees\nwhich\nare\nlevied\nfor\nthe\nrelevant\ninfrastructure\nunder\nArticle\n7\n(\n4\n)\nin\ncases\nwhere\n:\na\n)\nhe\ndoes\nnot\nproduce\na\ncapacity\nenhancement\nplan\n;\nor\nb\n)\nhe\ndoes\nnot\nmake\nprogress\nwith\nthe\naction\nplan\nidentified\nin\nthe\ncapacity\nenhancement\nplan\n.\nHowever\n,\nthe\ninfrastructure\nmanager\nmay\n,\nsubject\nto\nthe\napproval\nof\nthe\nregulatory\nbody\nreferred\nto\nin\nArticle\n30\ncontinue\nto\nlevy\nthose\nfees\nif\n:\na\n)\nthe\ncapacity\nenhancement\nplan\ncan\nnot\nbe\nrealised\nfor\nreasons\nbeyond\nhis\ncontrol\n;\nor\nb\n)\nthe\noptions\navailable\nare\nnot\neconomically\nor\nfinancially\nviable\n.\nArticle\n27\nUse\nof\ntrain\npaths\n1\n.\nIn\nparticular\nfor\ncongested\ninfrastructure\nthe\ninfrastructure\nmanager\nshall\nrequire\nthe\nsurrender\nof\na\ntrain\npath\nwhich\n,\nover\na\nperiod\nof\nat\nleast\none\nmonth\n,\nhas\nbeen\nused\nless\nthan\na\nthreshold\nquota\nto\nbe\nlaid\ndown\nin\nthe\nnetwork\nstatement\n,\nunless\nthis\nwas\ndue\nto\nnon-economic\nreasons\nbeyond\nthe\noperator\n's\ncontrol\n.\n2\n.\nAn\ninfrastructure\nmanager\nmay\nspecify\nin\nthe\nnetwork\nstatement\nconditions\nwhereby\nit\nwill\ntake\naccount\nof\nprevious\nlevels\nof\nutilisation\nof\ntrain\npaths\nin\ndetermining\npriorities\nfor\nthe\nallocation\nprocess\n.\nArticle\n28\nInfrastructure\ncapacity\nfor\nscheduled\nmaintenance\n1\n.\nRequests\nfor\ninfrastructure\ncapacity\nto\nenable\nmaintenance\nto\nbe\nperformed\nshall\nbe\nsubmitted\nduring\nthe\nscheduling\nprocess\n.\n2\n.\nAdequate\naccount\nshall\nbe\ntaken\nby\nthe\ninfrastructure\nmanager\nof\nthe\neffect\nof\ninfrastructure\ncapacity\nreserved\nfor\nscheduled\ntrack\nmaintenance\non\napplicants\n.\nArticle\n29\nSpecial\nmeasures\nto\nbe\ntaken\nin\nthe\nevent\nof\ndisturbance\n1\n.\nIn\nthe\nevent\nof\ndisturbance\nto\ntrain\nmovements\ncaused\nby\ntechnical\nfailure\nor\naccident\nthe\ninfrastructure\nmanager\nmust\ntake\nall\nnecessary\nsteps\nto\nrestore\nthe\nnormal\nsituation\n.\nTo\nthat\nend\nhe\nshall\ndraw\nup\na\ncontingency\nplan\nlisting\nthe\nvarious\npublic\nbodies\nto\nbe\ninformed\nin\nthe\nevent\nof\nserious\nincidents\nor\nserious\ndisturbance\nto\ntrain\nmovements\n.\n2\n.\nIn\nan\nemergency\nand\nwhere\nabsolutely\nnecessary\non\naccount\nof\na\nbreakdown\nmaking\nthe\ninfrastructure\ntemporarily\nunusable\n,\nthe\npaths\nallocated\nmay\nbe\nwithdrawn\nwithout\nwarning\nfor\nas\nlong\nas\nis\nnecessary\nto\nrepair\nthe\nsystem\n.\nThe\ninfrastructure\nmanager\nmay\n,\nif\nhe\ndeems\nit\nnecessary\n,\nrequire\nrailway\nundertakings\nto\nmake\navailable\nto\nhim\nthe\nresources\nwhich\nhe\nfeels\nare\nthe\nmost\nappropriate\nto\nrestore\nthe\nnormal\nsituation\nas\nsoon\nas\npossible\n.\n3\n.\nMember\nStates\nmay\nrequire\nrailway\nundertakings\nto\nbe\ninvolved\nin\nassuring\nthe\nenforcement\nand\nmonitoring\nof\ntheir\nown\ncompliance\nof\nthe\nsafety\nstandards\nand\nrules\n.\nCHAPTER\nIV\nGENERAL\nMEASURES\nArticle\n30\nRegulatory\nbody\n1\n.\nWithout\nprejudice\nto\nArticle\n21\n(\n6\n)\n,\nMember\nStates\nshall\nestablish\na\nregulatory\nbody\n.\nThis\nbody\n,\nwhich\ncan\nbe\nthe\nMinistry\nresponsible\nfor\ntransport\nmatters\nor\nany\nother\nbody\n,\nshall\nbe\nindependent\nin\nits\norganisation\n,\nfunding\ndecisions\n,\nlegal\nstructure\nand\ndecision-making\nfrom\nany\ninfrastructure\nmanager\n,\ncharging\nbody\n,\nallocation\nbody\nor\napplicant\n.\nThe\nbody\nshall\nfunction\naccording\nto\nthe\nprinciples\noutlined\nin\nthis\nArticle\nwhereby\nappeal\nand\nregulatory\nfunctions\nmay\nbe\nattributed\nto\nseparate\nbodies\n.\n2\n.\nAn\napplicant\nshall\nhave\na\nright\nto\nappeal\nto\nthe\nregulatory\nbody\nif\nit\nbelieves\nthat\nit\nhas\nbeen\nunfairly\ntreated\n,\ndiscriminated\nagainst\nor\nis\nin\nany\nother\nway\naggrieved\n,\nand\nin\nparticular\nagainst\ndecisions\nadopted\nby\nthe\ninfrastructure\nmanager\nor\nwhere\nappropriate\nthe\nrailway\nundertaking\nconcerning\n:\na\n)\nthe\nnetwork\nstatement\n;\nb\n)\ncriteria\ncontained\nwithin\nit\n;\nc\n)\nthe\nallocation\nprocess\nand\nits\nresult\n;\nd\n)\nthe\ncharging\nscheme\n;\ne\n)\nlevel\nor\nstructure\nof\ninfrastructure\nfees\nwhich\nit\nis\n,\nor\nmay\nbe\n,\nrequired\nto\npay\n;\nf\n)\nsafety\ncertificate\n,\nenforcement\nand\nmonitoring\nof\nthe\nsafety\nstandards\nand\nrules\n.\n3\n.\nThe\nregulatory\nbody\nshall\nensure\nthat\ncharges\nset\nby\nthe\ninfrastructure\nmanager\ncomply\nwith\nchapter\nII\nand\nare\nnon-discriminatory\n.\nNegotiation\nbetween\napplicants\nand\nan\ninfrastructure\nmanager\nconcerning\nthe\nlevel\nof\ninfrastructure\ncharges\nshall\nonly\nbe\npermitted\nif\nthese\nare\ncarried\nout\nunder\nthe\nsupervision\nof\nthe\nregulatory\nbody\n.\nThe\nregulatory\nbody\nshall\nintervene\nif\nnegotiations\nare\nlikely\nto\ncontravene\nthe\nrequirements\nof\nthis\nDirective\n.\n4\n.\nThe\nregulatory\nbody\nshall\nhave\nthe\npower\nto\nrequest\nrelevant\ninformation\nfrom\nthe\ninfrastructure\nmanager\n,\napplicants\nand\nany\nthird\nparty\ninvolved\nwithin\nthe\nMember\nState\nconcerned\n,\nwhich\nmust\nbe\nsupplied\nwithout\nundue\ndelay\n.\n5\n.\nThe\nregulatory\nbody\nshall\nbe\nrequired\nto\ndecide\non\nany\ncomplaints\nand\ntake\naction\nto\nremedy\nthe\nsituation\nwithin\na\nmaximum\nperiod\nof\ntwo\nmonths\nfrom\nreceipt\nof\nall\ninformation\n.\nNotwithstanding\nparagraph\n6\n,\na\ndecision\nof\nthe\nregulatory\nbody\nshall\nbe\nbinding\non\nall\nparties\ncovered\nby\nthat\ndecision\n.\nIn\nthe\nevent\nof\nan\nappeal\nagainst\na\nrefusal\nto\ngrant\ninfrastructure\ncapacity\n,\nor\nagainst\nthe\nterms\nof\nan\noffer\nof\ncapacity\n,\nthe\nregulatory\nbody\nshall\neither\nconfirm\nthat\nno\nmodification\nof\nthe\ninfrastructure\nmanager\n's\ndecision\nis\nrequired\n,\nor\nit\nshall\nrequire\nmodification\nof\nthat\ndecision\nin\naccordance\nwith\ndirections\nspecified\nby\nthe\nregulatory\nbody\n.\n6\n.\nMember\nStates\nshall\ntake\nthe\nmeasures\nnecessary\nto\nensure\nthat\ndecisions\ntaken\nby\nthe\nregulatory\nbody\nare\nsubject\nto\njudicial\nreview\n.\nArticle\n31\nCooperation\nof\nregulatory\nbodies\nThe\nnational\nregulatory\nbodies\nshall\nexchange\ninformation\nabout\ntheir\nwork\nand\ndecision-making\nprinciples\nand\npractice\nfor\nthe\npurpose\nof\ncoordinating\ntheir\ndecision-making\nprinciples\nacross\nthe\nCommunity\n.\nThe\nCommission\nshall\nsupport\nthem\nin\nthis\ntask\n.\nArticle\n32\nSafety\ncertification\n1\n.\nThe\narrangements\nfor\nsafety\ncertification\nfor\nrailway\nundertakings\nwhich\nare\nor\nwill\nbe\nestablished\nin\nthe\nCommunity\nand\nthe\ninternational\ngroupings\nwhich\nthey\nform\nshall\nbe\nin\naccordance\nwith\nthis\nArticle\n.\n2\n.\nThe\nMember\nStates\nshall\nprovide\nfor\ntheir\nrespective\nterritories\nthat\na\nsafety\ncertificate\nin\nwhich\nthe\nrailway\nundertakings\n'\nsafety\nrequirements\nare\nset\nout\nbe\nsubmitted\nin\norder\nto\nensure\nsafe\nservice\non\nthe\nroutes\nconcerned\n.\n3\n.\nIn\norder\nto\nobtain\nthe\nsafety\ncertificate\n,\nthe\nrailway\nundertaking\nshall\ncomply\nwith\nthe\nregulations\nunder\nnational\nlaw\n,\ncompatible\nwith\nCommunity\nlaw\nand\napplied\nin\na\nnon-discriminatory\nmanner\n,\nlaying\ndown\nthe\ntechnical\nand\noperational\nrequirements\nspecific\nto\nrail\nservices\nand\nthe\nsafety\nrequirements\napplying\nto\nstaff\n,\nrolling\nstock\nand\nthe\nundertaking\n's\ninternal\norganisation\n.\nIn\nparticular\n,\nit\nshall\nprovide\nproof\nthat\nthe\nstaff\nwhom\nit\nemploys\nto\noperate\nand\naccompany\nthe\ntrains\nhas\nthe\nnecessary\ntraining\nto\ncomply\nwith\nthe\ntraffic\nrules\napplied\nby\nthe\ninfrastructure\nmanager\nand\nto\nmeet\nthe\nsafety\nrequirements\nimposed\non\nit\nin\nthe\ninterests\nof\ntrain\nmovement\n.\nThe\nrailway\nundertaking\nshall\nalso\nprove\nthat\nthe\nrolling\nstock\nmaking\nup\nthe\ntrains\nhas\nbeen\napproved\nby\nthe\npublic\nauthority\nor\nby\nthe\ninfrastructure\nmanager\nand\nchecked\nin\naccordance\nwith\nthe\noperating\nrules\napplicable\nto\nthe\ninfrastructure\nused\n.\nThe\nsafety\ncertificate\nshall\nbe\nissued\nby\nwhichever\nbody\nis\ndesignated\nfor\nthe\npurpose\nby\nthe\nMember\nState\nin\nwhich\nthe\ninfrastructure\nused\nis\nsituated\n.\nArticle\n33\nDerogations\n1\n.\nFor\na\nperiod\nof\nfive\nyears\nfrom\n15\nMarch\n2003\n,\nthe\nfollowing\nMember\nStates\n:\n-\nIreland\n,\nas\na\nMember\nState\nlocated\non\nan\nisland\n,\nwith\na\nrail\nlink\nto\nonly\none\nother\nMember\nState\n,\n-\nthe\nUnited\nKingdom\n,\nin\nrespect\nof\nNorthern\nIreland\n,\non\nthe\nsame\nbasis\n,\nand\n-\nGreece\n,\nas\na\nMember\nState\nthat\ndoes\nnot\nhave\nany\ndirect\nrail\nlink\nto\nany\nother\nMember\nState\n,\ndo\nnot\nneed\nto\napply\nthe\nrequirements\nset\nout\nin\n:\na\n)\nArticles\n3\n,\n4\n(\n2\n)\n,\n13\n,\n14\n,\n17\n,\n21\n(\n4\n)\n,\n21\n(\n6\n)\n,\n22\n,\n24\n(\n3\n)\n,\n25\nto\n28\nand\n30\non\nthe\ncondition\nthat\ndecisions\non\nthe\nallocation\nof\ninfrastructure\ncapacity\nor\nthe\ncharging\nof\nfees\nare\nopen\nto\nappeal\n,\nwhen\nso\nrequested\nin\nwriting\nby\na\nrailway\nundertaking\n,\nbefore\nan\nindependent\nbody\nwhich\nshall\ntake\nits\ndecision\nwithin\ntwo\nmonths\nof\nthe\nsubmission\nof\nall\nrelevant\ninformation\nand\nwhose\ndecision\nshall\nbe\nsubject\nto\njudicial\nreview\n,\nand\nb\n)\nArticle\n32\nin\nso\nfar\nas\nrail\ntransport\nservices\nfalling\noutside\nthe\nscope\nof\nArticle\n10\nof\nDirective\n91/440/EEC\nare\nconcerned\n.\n2\n.\nHowever\n,\nwhere\n:\na\n)\nmore\nthan\none\nrailway\nundertaking\nlicensed\nin\naccordance\nwith\nArticle\n4\nof\nDirective\n95/18/EC\n,\nor\n,\nin\nthe\ncase\nof\nIreland\nand\nNorthern\nIreland\n,\na\nrailway\ncompany\nso\nlicensed\nelsewhere\nsubmits\nan\nofficial\napplication\nto\noperate\ncompeting\nrailway\nservices\nin\n,\nto\nor\nfrom\nIreland\n,\nNorthern\nIreland\nor\nGreece\n,\nthe\ncontinued\napplicability\nof\nthis\nderogation\nwill\nbe\ndecided\nupon\nin\naccordance\nwith\nthe\nadvisory\nprocedure\nreferred\nto\nin\nArticle\n35\n(\n2\n)\n;\nor\nb\n)\na\nrailway\nundertaking\noperating\nrailway\nservices\nin\nIreland\n,\nNorthern\nIreland\nor\nGreece\nsubmits\nan\nofficial\napplication\nto\noperate\nrailway\nservices\non\n,\nto\nor\nfrom\nthe\nterritory\nof\nanother\nMember\nState\n(\nin\nthe\ncase\nof\nIreland\n,\nor\nthe\nUnited\nKingdom\n,\nin\nrespect\nof\nNorthern\nIreland\n,\nor\nboth\n,\nanother\nMember\nState\noutside\ntheir\nterritories\n)\n,\nthe\nderogations\nreferred\nto\nin\nparagraph\n1\nshall\nnot\napply\n.\nWithin\none\nyear\nfrom\nthe\nreceipt\nof\neither\nthe\ndecision\nreferred\nto\nin\npoint\n(\na\n)\nadopted\nin\naccordance\nwith\nthe\nadvisory\nprocedure\nreferred\nto\nin\nArticle\n35\n(\n2\n)\n,\nor\nnotification\nof\nthe\nofficial\napplication\nreferred\nto\nin\npoint\n(\nb\n)\n,\nthe\nMember\nState\nor\nStates\nconcerned\n(\nIreland\n,\nthe\nUnited\nKingdom\nwith\nrespect\nto\nNorthern\nIreland\n,\nor\nGreece\n)\nshall\nput\nin\nplace\nlegislation\nto\nimplement\nthe\nArticles\nreferred\nto\nin\nparagraph\n1\n.\n3\n.\nA\nderogation\nreferred\nto\nin\nparagraph\n1\nmay\nbe\nrenewed\nfor\nperiods\nnot\nlonger\nthan\nfive\nyears\n.\nNot\nlater\nthan\n12\nmonths\nbefore\nthe\nexpiry\ndate\nof\nthe\nderogation\na\nMember\nState\navailing\nitself\nof\nsuch\nderogation\nmay\naddress\na\nrequest\nto\nthe\nCommission\nfor\na\nrenewed\nderogation\n.\nAny\nsuch\nrequest\nmust\nbe\nsubstantiated\n.\nThe\nCommission\nshall\nexamine\nsuch\na\nrequest\nand\nadopt\na\ndecision\nin\naccordance\nwith\nthe\nadvisory\nprocedure\nreferred\nto\nin\nArticle\n35\n(\n2\n)\n.\nThe\nsaid\nadvisory\nprocedure\nshall\napply\nto\nany\ndecision\nrelated\nto\nthe\nrequest\n.\nWhen\nadopting\nits\ndecision\nthe\nCommission\nshall\ntake\ninto\naccount\nany\ndevelopment\nin\nthe\ngeopolitical\nsituation\nand\nthe\ndevelopment\nof\nthe\nrail\nmarket\nin\n,\nfrom\nand\nto\nthe\nMember\nState\nhaving\nrequested\nthe\nrenewed\nderogation\n.\n4\n.\nLuxembourg\nas\na\nMember\nState\nwith\na\nrelatively\nsmall\nrail\nnetwork\ndoes\nnot\nneed\nto\napply\nuntil\n31\nAugust\n2004\nthe\nrequirement\nto\naward\nto\nan\nindependent\nbody\nthe\nfunctions\ndetermining\nequitable\nand\nnon-discriminatory\naccess\nto\ninfrastructure\n,\nas\nprovided\nfor\nin\nArticles\n4\nand\n14\nin\nso\nfar\nas\nthey\noblige\nMember\nStates\nto\nestablish\nindependent\nbodies\nperforming\nthe\ntasks\nreferred\nto\nin\nthose\nArticles\n.\nCHAPTER\nV\nFINAL\nPROVISIONS\nArticle\n34\nImplementing\nmeasures\n1\n.\nMember\nStates\nmay\nbring\nany\nquestion\nconcerning\nthe\nimplementation\nof\nthis\nDirective\nto\nthe\nattention\nof\nthe\nCommission\n.\nAppropriate\ndecisions\nshall\nbe\nadopted\nin\naccordance\nwith\nthe\nadvisory\nprocedure\nreferred\nto\nin\nArticle\n35\n(\n2\n)\n.\n2\n.\nAt\nthe\nrequest\nof\na\nMember\nState\nor\non\nits\nown\ninitiative\nthe\nCommission\nshall\n,\nin\na\nspecific\ncase\n,\nexamine\nthe\napplication\nand\nenforcement\nof\nprovisions\nconcerning\ncharging\n,\ncapacity\nallocation\nand\nsafety\ncertification\n,\nand\nwithin\ntwo\nmonths\nof\nreceipt\nof\nsuch\na\nrequest\ndecide\nin\naccordance\nwith\nthe\nadvisory\nprocedure\nreferred\nto\nin\nArticle\n35\n(\n2\n)\nwhether\nthe\nrelated\nmeasure\nmay\ncontinue\nto\nbe\napplied\n.\nThe\nCommission\nshall\ncommunicate\nits\ndecision\nto\nthe\nEuropean\nParliament\n,\nthe\nCouncil\nand\nto\nthe\nMember\nStates\n.\nWithout\nprejudice\nto\nArticle\n226\nof\nthe\nTreaty\n,\nany\nMember\nState\nmay\nrefer\nthe\nCommission\n's\ndecision\nto\nthe\nCouncil\nwithin\na\ntime\nlimit\nof\none\nmonth\n.\nThe\nCouncil\n,\nacting\nby\na\nqualified\nmajority\n,\nmay\nin\nexceptional\ncircumstances\ntake\na\ndifferent\ndecision\nwithin\na\nperiod\nof\none\nmonth\n.\n3\n.\nThe\namendments\nnecessary\nto\nadapt\nthe\nAnnexes\nshall\nbe\nadopted\nin\naccordance\nwith\nthe\nregulatory\nprocedure\nreferred\nto\nin\nArticle\n35\n(\n3\n)\n.\nArticle\n35\nCommittee\nprocedures\n1\n.\nThe\nCommission\nshall\nbe\nassisted\nby\na\nCommittee\n.\n2\n.\nWhere\nreference\nis\nmade\nto\nthis\nparagraph\n,\nArticles\n3\nand\n7\nof\nDecision\n1999/468/EC\nshall\napply\n,\nhaving\nregard\nto\nthe\nprovisions\nof\nArticle\n8\nthereof\n.\n3\n.\nWhere\nreference\nis\nmade\nto\nthis\nparagraph\n,\nArticles\n5\nand\n7\nof\nDecision\n1999/468/EC\nshall\napply\n,\nhaving\nregard\nto\nthe\nprovisions\nof\nArticle\n8\nthereof\n.\nThe\nperiod\nlaid\ndown\nin\nArticle\n5\n(\n6\n)\nof\nDecision\n1999/468/EC\nshall\nbe\nset\nat\nthree\nmonths\n.\n4\n.\nThe\nCommittee\nshall\nadopt\nits\nrules\nof\nprocedure\n.\nArticle\n36\nReport\nThe\nCommission\nshall\nby\n15\nMarch\n2005\nsubmit\nto\nthe\nEuropean\nParliament\nand\nto\nthe\nCouncil\na\nreport\non\nthe\nimplementation\nof\nthis\nDirective\n,\naccompanied\nif\nnecessary\nby\nproposals\nfor\nfurther\nCommunity\naction\n.\nArticle\n37\nRepeals\nRegulation\n(\nEEC\n)\nNo\n2830/77\n,\nRegulation\n(\nEEC\n)\nNo\n2183/78\n,\nDecision\n82/529/EEC\n,\nDecision\n83/418/EEC\nand\nDirective\n95/19/EC\nare\nhereby\nrepealed\n.\nArticle\n38\nImplementation\nThe\nMember\nStates\nshall\nbring\ninto\nforce\nthe\nlaws\n,\nregulations\nand\nadministrative\nprovisions\nnecessary\nto\ncomply\nwith\nthis\nDirective\nby\n15\nMarch\n2003\n.\nThey\nshall\nforthwith\ninform\nthe\nCommission\nthereof\n.\nWhen\nMember\nStates\nadopt\nthose\nprovisions\n,\nthey\nshall\ncontain\na\nreference\nto\nthis\nDirective\nor\nbe\naccompanied\nby\nsuch\nreference\non\nthe\noccasion\nof\ntheir\nofficial\npublication\n.\nMember\nStates\nshall\ndetermine\nhow\nsuch\nreference\nis\nto\nbe\nmade\n.\nArticle\n39\nEntry\ninto\nforce\nThis\nDirective\nshall\nenter\ninto\nforce\non\nthe\ndate\nof\nits\npublication\nin\nthe\nOfficial\nJournal\nof\nthe\nEuropean\nCommunities\n.\nANNEX\nI\nContents\nof\nthe\nnetwork\nstatement\nThe\nnetwork\nstatement\nreferred\nto\nin\nArticle\n3\nshall\ncontain\nthe\nfollowing\ninformation\n:\n1\n.\nA\nsection\nsetting\nout\nthe\nnature\nof\nthe\ninfrastructure\nwhich\nis\navailable\nto\nrailway\nundertakings\nand\nthe\nconditions\nof\naccess\nto\nit\n.\n2\n.\nA\nsection\non\ncharging\nprinciples\nand\ntariffs\n.\nThis\nshall\ncontain\nappropriate\ndetails\nof\nthe\ncharging\nscheme\nas\nwell\nas\nsufficient\ninformation\non\ncharges\nthat\napply\nto\nthe\nservices\nlisted\nin\nAnnex\nII\nwhich\nare\nprovided\nby\nonly\none\nsupplier\n.\nIt\nshall\ndetail\nthe\nmethodology\n,\nrules\nand\n,\nwhere\napplicable\n,\nscales\nused\nfor\nthe\napplication\nof\nArticle\n7\n(\n4\n)\nand\n(\n5\n)\nand\nArticles\n8\nand\n9\n.\nIt\nshall\ncontain\ninformation\non\nchanges\nin\ncharges\nalready\ndecided\nupon\nor\nforeseen\n.\n3\n.\nA\nsection\non\nthe\nprinciples\nand\ncriteria\nfor\ncapacity\nallocation\n.\nThis\nshall\nset\nout\nthe\ngeneral\ncapacity\ncharacteristics\nof\nthe\ninfrastructure\nwhich\nis\navailable\nto\nrailway\nundertakings\nand\nany\nrestrictions\nrelating\nto\nits\nuse\n,\nincluding\nlikely\ncapacity\nrequirements\nfor\nmaintenance\n.\nIt\nshall\nalso\nspecify\nthe\nprocedures\nand\ndeadlines\nwhich\nrelate\nto\nthe\ncapacity\nallocation\nprocess\n.\nIt\nshall\ncontain\nspecific\ncriteria\nwhich\nare\nemployed\nduring\nthat\nprocess\n,\nin\nparticular\n:\na\n)\nthe\nprocedures\naccording\nto\nwhich\napplicants\nmay\nrequest\ncapacity\nfrom\nthe\ninfrastructure\nmanager\n;\nb\n)\nthe\nrequirements\ngoverning\napplicants\n;\nc\n)\nthe\nschedule\nfor\nthe\napplication\nand\nallocation\nprocesses\n;\nd\n)\nthe\nprinciples\ngoverning\nthe\ncoordination\nprocess\n;\ne\n)\nthe\nprocedures\nwhich\nshall\nbe\nfollowed\nand\ncriteria\nused\nwhere\ninfrastructure\nis\ncongested\n;\nf\n)\ndetails\nof\nrestrictions\non\nthe\nuse\nof\ninfrastructure\n;\ng\n)\nany\nconditions\nby\nwhich\naccount\nis\ntaken\nof\nprevious\nlevels\nof\nutilisation\nof\ncapacity\nin\ndetermining\npriorities\nfor\nthe\nallocation\nprocess\n.\nIt\nshall\ndetail\nthe\nmeasures\ntaken\nto\nensure\nthe\nadequate\ntreatment\nof\nfreight\nservices\n,\ninternational\nservices\nand\nrequests\nsubject\nto\nthe\nad\nhoc\nprocedure\n.\nANNEX\nII\nServices\nto\nbe\nsupplied\nto\nthe\nrailway\nundertakings\n1\n.\nThe\nminimum\naccess\n
